{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486553339,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ud3gWEzhq52wiSSQPBw918Pc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\n8: \n9: !`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`\n\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\n!`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","text":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\n!`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":9,"totalLines":9,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/research.md","time":{"start":1783486553324,"end":1783486553337}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f6a9c96e52e328f016a4dd8594dfc819187c6b02ff34bde0c"}},"id":"prt_f40151ce9001bEvsAS5a4EInkM","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f4014faf0001L6OTGZyX9IaHde"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486553351,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_N5lWEGKnZGX6Po6FLgjfmJZo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research quick reference\"\n6:   - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"research iteration checklist\"\n8:   - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n9:   - \"research tuning guide\"\n10:   - \"research progress visualization\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: general\n13: version: 1.14.0.26\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Quick Reference\n17: \n18: One-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: Lookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n25: \n26: Operator contract source of truth for this page:\n27: - command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n28: - convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n29: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. COMMANDS\n34: \n35: | Command | Description |\n36: |---------|-------------|\n37: | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n38: | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n39: | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n40: \n41: ### Parameters\n42: \n43: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n44: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n45: | `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n46: | `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n47: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n48: | `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 3. WHEN TO USE\n53: \n54: | Scenario | Use |\n55: |----------|-----|\n56: | Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:research` |\n57: | Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n58: | Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n59: | Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:research --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n64: \n65: ```text\n66: /deep:research  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n67:     |                    |                      |\n68:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n69:     |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n70:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n71:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n72:     |                    |\n73:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n74:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n75:     |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n76:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 5. STATE FILES\n82: \n83: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n84: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n85: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n86: | State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n87: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n88: | Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n89: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n90: | Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n91: | Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n92: \n93: > **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n94: \n95: > **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n96: \n97: > **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n98: \n99: > **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n104: \n105: | Status | Meaning |\n106: |--------|---------|\n107: | `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n108: | `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n109: | `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n110: | `stuck` | No new information found |\n111: | `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n112: | `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n117: \n118: ```text\n119: Max iterations reached?\n120:   Yes --> STOP\n121: \n122: All questions answered?\n123:   Yes --> STOP\n124: \n125: stuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n126:   Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n127:     Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n128:     Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n129: \n130: Composite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n131:   Yes --> STOP (converged)\n132: \n133: Otherwise --> CONTINUE\n134: ```\n135: \n136: ### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n137: \n138: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n139: |--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n140: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n141: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n142: | Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n143: \n144: **Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n145: \n146: Quality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n151: \n152: Each @deep-research iteration:\n153: 1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n154: 2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n155: 3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n156: 4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n157: 5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n158: 6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n159: 7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n164: \n165: | Goal | Adjustment |\n166: |------|------------|\n167: | Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n168: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n169: | Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n170: | Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n175: \n176: | Problem | Fix |\n177: |---------|-----|\n178: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n179: | Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n180: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n181: | State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n182: | Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n187: \n188: After each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n189: \n190: ### Format\n191: \n192: | Element | Format | Example |\n193: |---------|--------|---------|\n194: | newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n195: | Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n196: | Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n197: | Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n198: \n199: ### Example Output\n200: \n201: ```text\n202: ITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n203: ─────────────────────\n204: newInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\n205: Questions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\n206: Composite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\n207: Noise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\n208: Stuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\n209: Signals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### When to Display\n213: \n214: - After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n215: - In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n216: - In confirm mode approval gates\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## 12. RELATED\n221: \n222: | Resource | Purpose |\n223: |----------|---------|\n224: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n225: | `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n226: | `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n227: | `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n228: | `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n229: | `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## 13. REVIEW MODE\n234: \n235: Review mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research quick reference\"\n  - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"research iteration checklist\"\n  - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n  - \"research tuning guide\"\n  - \"research progress visualization\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.26\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research quick reference\"\n  - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"research iteration checklist\"\n  - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n  - \"research tuning guide\"\n  - \"research progress visualization\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.26\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n\nOperator contract source of truth for this page:\n- command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n\n---\n\n## 2. COMMANDS\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n\n---\n\n## 3. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:research` |\n| Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n| Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n| Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:research --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```text\n/deep:research  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. STATE FILES\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n| State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n| Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n| Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n| Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n\n> **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n\n> **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n\n> **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n\n> **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n| `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n| `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n| `stuck` | No new information found |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n\n```text\nMax iterations reached?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nAll questions answered?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nstuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n  Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n    Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n    Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n\nComposite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n  Yes --> STOP (converged)\n\nOtherwise --> CONTINUE\n```\n\n### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n|--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n| Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n\n**Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n\nQuality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n\n---\n\n## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-research iteration:\n1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n\n---\n\n## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n| Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n| Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n| State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n| Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n\nAfter each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n\n### Format\n\n| Element | Format | Example |\n|---------|--------|---------|\n| newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n| Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n| Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n| Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n\n### Example Output\n\n```text\nITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n─────────────────────\nnewInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\nQuestions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\nComposite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\nNoise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\nStuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\nSignals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n```\n\n### When to Display\n\n- After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n- In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n- In confirm mode approval gates\n\n---\n\n## 12. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n| `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n| `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n| `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n| `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n| `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n\n---\n\n## 13. REVIEW MODE\n\nReview mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":235,"totalLines":235,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1783486553346,"end":1783486553350}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f6a9c96e52e328f016a4dd8594e088191bb6c51145e4636e8"}},"id":"prt_f40151cfe001HK4LN5Uxi8PDND","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f4014faf0001L6OTGZyX9IaHde"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486553361,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_V6YPdrJZeQYfrQEFBs3mfV3s","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"research loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n9:   - \"research pause sentinel\"\n10:   - \"research synthesis phase\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\n17: \n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n35: \n36: ### Phase Model\n37: \n38: The deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n39: \n40: Runtime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n41: - Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n42: - Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n46: │  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n47: │          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n48: │ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n49: │ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n50: │ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n51: │          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n52: │          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n53: │          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n54: │          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n55: └──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n61: \n62: ### Purpose\n63: Set up all state files for a new research session.\n64: \n65: ### Steps\n66: \n67: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n68:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n69:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n70:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n71:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n72: 2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n73:    - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n74:    - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n75:    - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n76: 3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n77: 4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n78: 5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n79: 6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n80:    - Topic from user input\n81:    - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n82:    - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n83:    - Research boundaries from config\n84: 6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n85:    - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n86:    - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n87:    - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n88:    - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n89:    - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n90:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n91: 7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n92: 7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n93:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n94:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n95:    - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n96:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n97:    - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n98: 8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n99: \n100: ### Outputs\n101: - `research/deep-research-config.json`\n102: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n103: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n104: \n105: ### Auto-Resume Protocol\n106: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n107: 1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n108: 2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n109: 3. Read strategy.md for current state\n110: 4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n111: 5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n112: \n113: ```json\n114: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n115: ```\n116: \n117: 6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n118: \n119: ### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n120: \n121: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n122: \n123: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n124: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n125: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n126: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n127: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n128: \n129: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n130: \n131: ```json\n132: {\n133:   \"type\": \"event\",\n134:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n135:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n136:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n137:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n138:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n139:   \"generation\": <number>,\n140:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n141:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n142:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n151: \n152: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n153: \n154: #### Step 1: Read State\n155: - Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n156: - Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n157: \n158: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n159: Run the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n160: - Max iterations reached? STOP\n161: - Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n162: - Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n163: - All questions answered? STOP\n164: - Otherwise: CONTINUE\n165: \n166: #### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n167: \n168: When the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n169: 1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n170: 2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n171: 3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n172: 4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n173:    - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n174:    - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n175:    - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n176: 5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n177: 6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n178: \n179: If the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n180: \n181: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n182: \n183: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n184: \n185: 1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n186: 2. If present:\n187:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n188:    - Halt the loop with message:\n189:      ```text\n190:      Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n191:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n192:      ```\n193:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n194: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n195:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n196:    - Continue from step_read_state\n197: \n198: Pause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n199: \n200: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n201: \n202: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n203: \n204: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n205: \n206: ```text\n207: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n208: Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\n209: Questions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n210: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n211: Recovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\n212: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n213: ```\n214: \n215: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n216: \n217: #### Step 2d: Rejected Pattern Cache Check\n218: \n219: Before selecting the next-focus, recovery, or ideas-backed candidate for dispatch, read the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache and promoted ideas backlog from the findings registry.\n220: \n221: Rejected-cache lifecycle:\n222: \n223: 1. `idea_rejected` appends one rejected pattern to JSONL with `ideaId`, `idea` or `pattern`, optional `category`, optional `reason`, and normal lifecycle fields.\n224: 2. The reducer derives the active cache from JSONL events; generated registry and dashboard files expose `rejectedPatterns`, `rejectedPatternIndex`, and `suppressedCandidates`.\n225: 3. Exact suppression compares normalized candidate text against normalized rejected text.\n226: 4. Fuzzy suppression uses `rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold` from config when present, otherwise `0.85`, and only applies when the rejected category is compatible with the candidate category.\n227: 5. `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single active pattern by id or by pattern/category.\n228: 6. `ideaRejectedReset` clears all active rejected patterns for the current replay.\n229: \n230: The active cache is capped at 100 entries. When the replay would exceed that cap, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning. Operators can re-add an evicted pattern with another `idea_rejected` event if it remains relevant. Existing `ideaRejected` replay rows are legacy aliases and remain accepted for backward compatibility.\n231: \n232: Ideas lifecycle:\n233: \n234: 1. Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` events only. They must not append `idea_promoted`.\n235: 2. The reducer accumulates observations by `ideaId` or a normalized text-derived id.\n236: 3. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to `1..10`.\n237: 4. When an idea reaches `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`, the reducer appends one idempotent `idea_promoted` event and ranks promoted ideas by observation count, latest observation, then first observation.\n238: 5. `idea_rejected` removes the matching idea from `promotedIdeas` and from ideas-backed next-focus candidates until a reset/removal event clears the active rejected pattern.\n239: \n240: Candidate categories:\n241: \n242: | Category | Candidate source |\n243: |----------|------------------|\n244: | `next-focus` | Strategy next-focus, carried-forward open questions, open questions, and follow-up findings |\n245: | `recovery` | Stuck and blocked-stop recovery strategies |\n246: | `ideas` | Reducer-promoted ideas backlog entries |\n247: | `general` | Cross-category fallback when a narrower category is not known |\n248: \n249: When all candidates in a category are suppressed, continue with the next eligible category or halt for operator input rather than reusing the rejected idea.\n250: \n251: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n252: Dispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n253: ```text\n254: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n255: \n256: Research Topic: {config.topic}\n257: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n258: Focus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\n259: Remaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\n260: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 646. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research loop protocol\"\n  - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n  - \"research loop initialization\"\n  - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n  - \"research pause sentinel\"\n  - \"research synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research loop protocol\"\n  - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n  - \"research loop initialization\"\n  - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n  - \"research pause sentinel\"\n  - \"research synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n### Phase Model\n\nThe deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n\nRuntime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n- Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n```text\n┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n│          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n│ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n│ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n│ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n│          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n└──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\nSet up all state files for a new research session.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n   - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n   - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n   - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n   - Topic from user input\n   - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n   - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n   - Research boundaries from config\n6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n   - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n   - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n   - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n   - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n   - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n\n### Outputs\n- `research/deep-research-config.json`\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n\n### Auto-Resume Protocol\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n3. Read strategy.md for current state\n4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n```\n\n6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n\n### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n- Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n- Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\nRun the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n- Max iterations reached? STOP\n- Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n- Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n- All questions answered? STOP\n- Otherwise: CONTINUE\n\n#### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n\nWhen the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n   - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n   - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n\nIf the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```text\n     Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\nPause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```text\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\nSegment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\nQuestions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nRecovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n\n#### Step 2d: Rejected Pattern Cache Check\n\nBefore selecting the next-focus, recovery, or ideas-backed candidate for dispatch, read the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache and promoted ideas backlog from the findings registry.\n\nRejected-cache lifecycle:\n\n1. `idea_rejected` appends one rejected pattern to JSONL with `ideaId`, `idea` or `pattern`, optional `category`, optional `reason`, and normal lifecycle fields.\n2. The reducer derives the active cache from JSONL events; generated registry and dashboard files expose `rejectedPatterns`, `rejectedPatternIndex`, and `suppressedCandidates`.\n3. Exact suppression compares normalized candidate text against normalized rejected text.\n4. Fuzzy suppression uses `rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold` from config when present, otherwise `0.85`, and only applies when the rejected category is compatible with the candidate category.\n5. `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single active pattern by id or by pattern/category.\n6. `ideaRejectedReset` clears all active rejected patterns for the current replay.\n\nThe active cache is capped at 100 entries. When the replay would exceed that cap, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning. Operators can re-add an evicted pattern with another `idea_rejected` event if it remains relevant. Existing `ideaRejected` replay rows are legacy aliases and remain accepted for backward compatibility.\n\nIdeas lifecycle:\n\n1. Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` events only. They must not append `idea_promoted`.\n2. The reducer accumulates observations by `ideaId` or a normalized text-derived id.\n3. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to `1..10`.\n4. When an idea reaches `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`, the reducer appends one idempotent `idea_promoted` event and ranks promoted ideas by observation count, latest observation, then first observation.\n5. `idea_rejected` removes the matching idea from `promotedIdeas` and from ideas-backed next-focus candidates until a reset/removal event clears the active rejected pattern.\n\nCandidate categories:\n\n| Category | Candidate source |\n|----------|------------------|\n| `next-focus` | Strategy next-focus, carried-forward open questions, open questions, and follow-up findings |\n| `recovery` | Stuck and blocked-stop recovery strategies |\n| `ideas` | Reducer-promoted ideas backlog entries |\n| `general` | Cross-category fallback when a narrower category is not known |\n\nWhen all candidates in a category are suppressed, continue with the next eligible category or halt for operator input rather than reusing the rejected idea.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\nDispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n```text\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nResearch Topic: {config.topic}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\nRemaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":646,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1783486553355,"end":1783486553359}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f6a9c96e52e328f016a4dd8594e108191a1d607a607fd3692"}},"id":"prt_f40151d02001btb3tSf2PyPVj4","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f4014faf0001L6OTGZyX9IaHde"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486553365,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5PZYEpIs1NcCCRpMHfXAwNrk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: State Format Reference\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state format\"\n6:   - \"research state packet hub\"\n7:   - \"research file ownership model\"\n8:   - \"research file protection rules\"\n9:   - \"research packet location\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # State Format Reference\n16: \n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n30: \n31: ### Routed Details\n32: \n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n36: \n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n38: \n39: ### Packet Summary\n40: \n41: The deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n42: \n43: | File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n44: |------|--------|---------|------------|\n45: | `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n46: | `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n47: | `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n48: | `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n49: | `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n50: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n51: | `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n52: | `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n53: | `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n54: \n55: The artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n60: \n61: Root specs use:\n62: \n63: ```text\n64: {spec_folder}/research/\n65: ```\n66: \n67: Child-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n68: \n69: - first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n70: - a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n71: - continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n72: \n73: This avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n78: \n79: | Owner | Writes |\n80: |-------|--------|\n81: | Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n82: | Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n83: | Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n84: | Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n85: \n86: The reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n91: \n92: | Protection | Meaning |\n93: |------------|---------|\n94: | `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n95: | `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n96: | `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n97: | `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n98: | `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n99: \n100: The config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n105: \n106: | Resource | Use When |\n107: |----------|----------|\n108: | `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n109: | `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n110: | `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n111: | `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n112: | `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n117: \n118: - Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n119: - Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n120: - Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.\n\n(End of file - total 120 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSummarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n\n### Routed Details\n\n- `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n- `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n- `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n\nFor iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n\n### Packet Summary\n\nThe deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n\n| File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n|------|--------|---------|------------|\n| `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n| `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n| `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n| `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n| `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n| `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n| `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n| `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n\nThe artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n\nRoot specs use:\n\n```text\n{spec_folder}/research/\n```\n\nChild-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n\n- first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n- a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n- continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n\nThis avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n\n| Owner | Writes |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n| Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n| Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n| Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n\nThe reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n\n| Protection | Meaning |\n|------------|---------|\n| `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n| `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n| `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n| `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n| `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n\nThe config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n| `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n| `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n| `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n| `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n- Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n- Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":120,"totalLines":120,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1783486553360,"end":1783486553364}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f6a9c96e52e328f016a4dd8594e1481918b79039823d34089"}},"id":"prt_f40151d0c001NSOspFKF1ZRYcr","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f4014faf0001L6OTGZyX9IaHde"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783486553695,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"id":"prt_f40151e5d001HT0pv7kzsn1kRJ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"c6d101db0e4553dfd780695c86ca401b2aba19e2","messageID":"msg_f4014faf0001L6OTGZyX9IaHde","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28223,"input":7883,"output":249,"reasoning":123,"cache":{"write":0,"read":19968}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783486554921,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"id":"prt_f40152328001PLoipiRQyqpRPq","messageID":"msg_f40151fa3001n3txDZ0YVWFh2P","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","snapshot":"c6d101db0e4553dfd780695c86ca401b2aba19e2","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486561831,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5uXgUbNcMcX3INIWHj21KzyJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":251,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n251: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n252: Dispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n253: ```text\n254: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n255: \n256: Research Topic: {config.topic}\n257: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n258: Focus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\n259: Remaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\n260: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\n261: Resource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\n262: State Files:\n263:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n264:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n265:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\n266: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n267: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n268: ```\n269: \n270: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n271: \n272: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n273: \n274: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n275: - `cli-opencode` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `opencode run --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n276: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n277: \n278: All branches share:\n279: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n280: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n281: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n282: \n283: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n284: \n285: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n286: \n287: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n288: \n289: The dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n290: \n291: #### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n292: \n293: After dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n294: - **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n295: - **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n296: - If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n297:   1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n298:   2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n299:   3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n300: - Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n301: \n302: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n303: After agent completes:\n304: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n305: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n306: 3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n307:    - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n308:    - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n309: 4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n310: 5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n311: 6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n312: 7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n313: \n314: #### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n315: \n316: After evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n317: \n318: 1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n319: 2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n320:    - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n321:    - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n322:    - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n323:    - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n324:    - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n325:    - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n326: 3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n327: 4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n328: 5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n329: 6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n330: \n331: In **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n332: \n333: #### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n334: \n335: This checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n336: \n337: After each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n338: \n339: 1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n340:    ```bash\n341:    git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n342:    git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n343:    git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n344:    git add research/findings-registry.json\n345:    git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n346:    git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n347:    ```\n348: 2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n349: 3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n350: 4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n351: \n352: Checkpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n353: \n354: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n355: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n356: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n357: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n358: \n359: ### Ideas Backlog Convention\n360: \n361: The canonical ideas backlog is reducer-owned and derived from JSONL lifecycle events. A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` may still exist as operator-authored context, but leaf agents record new machine-discovered tangents with `idea_observed` events.\n362: \n363: #### Check Points\n364: \n365: The orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n366: \n367: 1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it as operator-authored context and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n368: 2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check reducer-promoted ideas before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Promoted ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n369: 3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read JSONL, registry, strategy.md, and any operator-authored ideas file to restore full context\n370: \n371: #### Event Format\n372: \n373: ```json\n374: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_observed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":4,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"source\":\"iteration-004.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"}\n375: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_promoted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":5,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"observationCount\":2,\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"firstObservedRun\":4,\"lastObservedRun\":5,\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:01:00Z\"}\n376: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_rejected\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":6,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"reason\":\"Operator rejected this direction\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"}\n377: ```\n378: \n379: Users can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents do not promote ideas directly; they emit observations, and the reducer owns promotion, ranking, rejection filtering, and dashboard projection.\n380: \n381: ### Stuck Recovery Protocol\n382: When stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n383: \n384: **Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\n385: Before selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n386: 1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n387: 2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n388:    - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n389:    - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n390:    - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n391:    - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n392:    - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n393: 3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n394: 4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n395: \n396: **Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n397: 1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n398: 2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n399: 3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n400: 4. Reset stuck counter\n401: 5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n402: \n403: ### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n404: \n405: When agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n406: \n407: 1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n408: 2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n409: 3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n410:    - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n411:    - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n412:    - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n413:    - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n414:    - Update strategy.md\n415:    - Append iteration record to JSONL\n416: 4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n417: 5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n418: \n419: **Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n424: \n425: An optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n426: \n427: ### When to Use Waves\n428: \n429: - 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n430: - Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n431: - Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n432: \n433: ### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n434: \n435: ```text\n436: Wave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n437:   |\n438:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n439:   +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n440:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n441:   |\n442: Scoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n443:   |\n444: Wave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n445:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n446:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n447:   |\n448: Repeat until convergence\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Scoring and Pruning\n452: \n453: In a future wave-enabled runtime:\n454: 1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n455: 2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n456: 3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n457: 4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n458: 5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n459: \n460: ### Breakthrough Detection\n461: \n462: When any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n463: \n464: 1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n465: 2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n466: 3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n467: 4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n468: \n469: ### Wave JSONL Records\n470: \n471: Wave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n472: \n473: ### Integration with Sequential Loop\n474: \n475: - Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n476: - The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n477: - A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n478: - The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n483: \n484: An alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n485: \n486: ### Motivation\n487: \n488: The standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n489: \n490: ### Dispatch Mechanism\n491: \n492: Replace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n493: \n494: 1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n495:    - Strategy.md (current state)\n496:    - Config.json (parameters)\n497:    - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n498:    - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n499:    - Full agent protocol instructions\n500: 2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n501: 3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n502: 4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n503: 5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n504: 6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n505: \n506: ### Trade-offs\n507: \n508: | Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n509: |--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n510: | Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n\n(Showing lines 251-510 of 646. Use offset=511 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\nDispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n```text\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nResearch Topic: {config.topic}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\nRemaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\nResource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\nDispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n```text\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nResearch Topic: {config.topic}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\nRemaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\nResource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-opencode` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `opencode run --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\nThe dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n\n#### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n\nAfter dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n- **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n- **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n- If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n  1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n  2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n  3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n- Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\nAfter agent completes:\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n   - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n   - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n\nAfter evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n\n1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n   - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n   - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n   - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n   - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n   - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n   - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n\nIn **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n\n#### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nThis checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n\nAfter each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n\n1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n   ```bash\n   git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n   git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n   git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n   git add research/findings-registry.json\n   git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n   git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n   ```\n2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n\nCheckpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Ideas Backlog Convention\n\nThe canonical ideas backlog is reducer-owned and derived from JSONL lifecycle events. A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` may still exist as operator-authored context, but leaf agents record new machine-discovered tangents with `idea_observed` events.\n\n#### Check Points\n\nThe orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n\n1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it as operator-authored context and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check reducer-promoted ideas before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Promoted ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read JSONL, registry, strategy.md, and any operator-authored ideas file to restore full context\n\n#### Event Format\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_observed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":4,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"source\":\"iteration-004.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_promoted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":5,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"observationCount\":2,\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"firstObservedRun\":4,\"lastObservedRun\":5,\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:01:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_rejected\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":6,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"reason\":\"Operator rejected this direction\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"}\n```\n\nUsers can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents do not promote ideas directly; they emit observations, and the reducer owns promotion, ranking, rejection filtering, and dashboard projection.\n\n### Stuck Recovery Protocol\nWhen stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n\n**Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\nBefore selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n   - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n   - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n   - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n   - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n   - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n\n**Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n4. Reset stuck counter\n5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n\n### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nWhen agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n\n1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n   - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n   - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n   - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n   - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - Update strategy.md\n   - Append iteration record to JSONL\n4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n\n**Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n\n### When to Use Waves\n\n- 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n- Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n- Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n\n### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n\n```text\nWave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n  |\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n  +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n  |\nScoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n  |\nWave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n  |\nRepeat until convergence\n```\n\n### Scoring and Pruning\n\nIn a future wave-enabled runtime:\n1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n\n### Breakthrough Detection\n\nWhen any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n\n1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n\n### Wave JSONL Records\n\nWave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n\n### Integration with Sequential Loop\n\n- Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n- The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n- A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n- The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n\n### Motivation\n\nThe standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n\n### Dispatch Mechanism\n\nReplace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n\n1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n   - Strategy.md (current state)\n   - Config.json (parameters)\n   - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n   - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n   - Full agent protocol instructions\n2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n\n### Trade-offs\n\n| Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n|--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |","lineStart":251,"lineEnd":510,"totalLines":646,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1783486561825,"end":1783486561830}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00bfd3abaa352977016a4dd861d20c8191a227ede89352e613"}},"id":"prt_f40153e1e001zlFbKCEzZovPBw","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40151fa3001n3txDZ0YVWFh2P"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486561856,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WJZtAews7JaoF2bFNQTY5ZXB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n58: \n59: ### stopReason Values\n60: \n61: | Value | When It Is Used |\n62: |-------|-----------------|\n63: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n64: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n65: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n66: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n67: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n68: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n69: \n70: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n71: \n72: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n73: \n74: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n75: |------------------------|------------------|\n76: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n77: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n78: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n79: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n80: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n81: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n82: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n87: \n88: ### Decision Order\n89: \n90: ```text\n91: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n92: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n93: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n94: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n95: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n96: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n97: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n98: 8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Composite Signal Weights\n102: \n103: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n104: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n105: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n106: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n107: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n108: \n109: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n114: \n115: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n116: \n117: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n118: |------|------|---------|\n119: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n120: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n121: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n122: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n123: \n124: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n129: \n130: | Resource | Use When |\n131: |----------|----------|\n132: | `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n133: | `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n134: | `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n135: | `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n136: | `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n137: | `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n142: \n143: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n144: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n145: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1783486561852,"end":1783486561855}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00bfd3abaa352977016a4dd861d21c8191ae852f44b8c539eb"}},"id":"prt_f40153e22001itBTLCr9fj8BAq","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40151fa3001n3txDZ0YVWFh2P"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486561881,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3VF0D460dE3AtBsqNfDLurTi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1783486561874,"end":1783486561878}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00bfd3abaa352977016a4dd861d22c8191a5871a86cb7fba90"}},"id":"prt_f40153e500011HaXcfy3AqHSun","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40151fa3001n3txDZ0YVWFh2P"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486561881,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_pq68L1V18l8T6vcW6Z1J5Af2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"research config record\"\n7:   - \"research iteration records\"\n8:   - \"research negative knowledge\"\n9:   - \"research graph events\"\n10:   - \"research event records\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n17: \n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n39: \n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"type\": \"config\",\n45:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n46:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n47:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n48:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n49:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n50:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n51: }\n52: ```\n53: \n54: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n59: \n60: ```json\n61: {\n62:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n63:   \"run\": 1,\n64:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n65:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n66:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n67:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n68:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n69:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n70:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n71:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n72:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: | Field | Required | Notes |\n77: |-------|----------|-------|\n78: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n79: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n80: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n81: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n82: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n83: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n84: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n85: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n86: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n87: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n88: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n89: \n90: Status values:\n91: \n92: | Status | Meaning |\n93: |--------|---------|\n94: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n95: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n96: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n97: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n98: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n99: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n104: \n105: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n106: \n107: ```json\n108: {\n109:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n110:   \"run\": 5,\n111:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n112:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n113:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n114:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n115:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n116:   }\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n125: \n126: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n127: \n128: ```json\n129: {\n130:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n131:   \"run\": 3,\n132:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n133:   \"ruledOut\": [\n134:     {\n135:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n136:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n137:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n138:     }\n139:   ]\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n148: \n149: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n150: \n151: ```json\n152: {\n153:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n154:   \"run\": 4,\n155:   \"graphEvents\": [\n156:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n157:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n158:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n159:   ]\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n168: \n169: Lifecycle event:\n170: \n171: ```json\n172: {\n173:   \"type\": \"event\",\n174:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n175:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n176:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n177:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n178:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n179:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n180:   \"generation\": 1,\n181:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n182:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: Blocked stop event:\n187: \n188: ```json\n189: {\n190:   \"type\": \"event\",\n191:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n192:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n193:   \"run\": 7,\n194:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n195:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n196:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n197:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Pause event:\n202: \n203: ```json\n204: {\n205:   \"type\": \"event\",\n206:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n207:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n208:   \"run\": 7,\n209:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n210:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n211:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: Stuck recovery event:\n216: \n217: ```json\n218: {\n219:   \"type\": \"event\",\n220:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n221:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n222:   \"run\": 7,\n223:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n224:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n225:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n226:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n227:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Idea observation event:\n232: \n233: ```json\n234: {\n235:   \"type\": \"event\",\n236:   \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n237:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n238:   \"run\": 7,\n239:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n240:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n241:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n242:   \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n243:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n248: \n249: Idea promotion event:\n250: \n251: ```json\n252: {\n253:   \"type\": \"event\",\n254:   \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n255:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n256:   \"run\": 8,\n257:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n258:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n259:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n260:   \"observationCount\": 2,\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 325. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nIdea observation event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nLeaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n\nIdea promotion event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 8,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"observationCount\": 2,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":325,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1783486561871,"end":1783486561879}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00bfd3abaa352977016a4dd861d224819199c29039e54fa97b"}},"id":"prt_f40153e45001tV7Mrf4KUszdd1","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40151fa3001n3txDZ0YVWFh2P"}}
