{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486731474,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_JQOGrLrEWxcQNXJfm0bGeHqP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"deep-loop-runtime","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows","include":"*.{cjs,ts,json,md,yaml}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:\n  Line 4: description: \"Unified deep-loop workflow skill: routes active requests to research, review, ai-council, and improvement modes over the shared deep-loop-runtime backend.\"\n\n  Line 12: One skill, four active workflow families, one shared backend. `deep-loop-workflows` is the public, advisor-routable home for active deep-loop personas; `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend it consumes. This hub holds NO per-mode convergence, state, or synthesis logic — each active mode keeps its own contract in its packet, and the hub only routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`.\n\n  Line 31: - Backend/runtime support (executor, coverage-graph, scoring, fan-out) — that is `deep-loop-runtime`, consumed here, not invoked as a user workflow.\n\n  Line 43: - **`runtimeLoopType`** — the graph-backed convergence key consumed by `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` (validated against active `research|review|council`). **Explicit `null` for all four improvement lanes; never inferred from `workflowMode`.** Note `ai-council` maps to `runtimeLoopType: council`.\n\n  Line 85: All modes consume `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free): executor config, prompt-pack, validation, atomic state, coverage-graph, Bayesian scoring, fan-out, the council primitives, and the promoted plumbing (capability resolver, artifact-root, loop-lock CLI, lifecycle taxonomy). The runtime never gains an `improvement` loopType — improvement stays host-driven.\n\n  Line 99: - **NEVER** add an `improvement` `loopType` to `deep-loop-runtime/convergence.cjs` (improvement is host-driven; `runtimeLoopType` stays `null`).\n\n  Line 112: - Backend: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` (frozen, consumed by every mode).\n\n  Line 138: - `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend every mode consumes.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/deep_ai_council_config.json:\n  Line 37:     \"owner\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md:\n  Line 126: - `scripts/` contains deterministic helpers; scripts are invoked explicitly and are not markdown-routed. Notable entries: `persist-artifacts.cjs` (artifact writer CLI), `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` (DAC-025 derived-projection rebuild — reads `ai-council-state.jsonl` and writes through `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --loop-type council`, with `--dry-run` for payload inspection).\n\n  Line 390:    - Graph updates belong to caller-owned `deep-loop-runtime` CLI reducers, not council-seat deliberation.\n\n  Line 411: - `references/convergence/deep_mode.md` - deep-mode session/topic/round hierarchy, state files, cost guards and the deep-loop-runtime dependency.\n\n  Line 483: - `references/integration/graph_support.md` - derived graph support and deep-loop-runtime CLI boundary.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:\n  Line 26:   node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --loop-type council\n\n  Line 56:       && fs.existsSync(path.join(current, '.opencode', 'skills', 'deep-loop-runtime', 'scripts', 'upsert.cjs'))\n\n  Line 65:     || path.join(repoRoot, '.opencode', 'skills', 'deep-loop-runtime', 'scrip