{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486764650,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mFdlqo7L9QgLhwEk04fbuIBw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy\n2: \n3: ## Research Topic\n4: \n5: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n6: \n7: ## Known Context\n8: \n9: - Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n10: - Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n11: - `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n12: - This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n13: - Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n14: \n15: ## Key Questions\n16: \n17: - [ ] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n18: - [ ] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n19: - [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n20: - [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n21: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n22: \n23: ## Answered Questions\n24: \n25: - None yet.\n26: \n27: ## What Worked\n28: \n29: - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n30: \n31: ## What Failed\n32: \n33: - None yet.\n34: \n35: ## Exhausted Approaches\n36: \n37: - None yet.\n38: \n39: ## Ruled-Out Directions\n40: \n41: - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n42: \n43: ## Non-Goals\n44: \n45: - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n46: - Do not rename `/deep:*` commands or agent names as part of the recommendation unless evidence shows a blocking contradiction.\n47: \n48: ## Stop Conditions\n49: \n50: - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n51: \n52: ## Next Focus\n53: \n54: Structural layout and identity model: validate that nesting runtime under a renamed hub as `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is the least-risk layout and that `runtime/` should not be a mode packet.\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n- Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n- [ ] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n- [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n- [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n- Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n- [ ] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n- [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n- [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n\n## Answered Questions\n\n- None yet.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n\n## What Failed\n\n- None yet.\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n- None yet.\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n- Do not rename `/deep:*` commands or agent names as part of the recommendation unless evidence shows a blocking contradiction.\n\n## Stop Conditions\n\n- Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nStructural layout and identity model: validate that nesting runtime under a renamed hub as `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is the least-risk layout and that `runtime/` should not be a mode packet.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":54,"totalLines":54,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783486764644,"end":1783486764649}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bbc1e8a43b977e0016a4dd92c9e808191828214e70aa69221"}},"id":"prt_f4018565f001HaFfbdGGc23jgi","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f401822f5001jZUglwzq5tHo63"}}
