encode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -13,33 +13,35 @@\n - Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n \n ## Key Questions\n \n-- [ ] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n+- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n - [ ] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n - [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n - [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n-- None yet.\n+- `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n+- Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n-- None yet.\n+- No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n \n ## Exhausted Approaches\n \n - None yet.\n \n ## Ruled-Out Directions\n \n - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n+- Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n \n ## Non-Goals\n \n - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n@@ -50,5 +52,5 @@\n - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Structural layout and identity model: validate that nesting runtime under a renamed hub as `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is the least-risk layout and that `runtime/` should not be a mode packet.\n+Bidirectional path-coupling repair: validate Class A (`runtime` to workflows content) and Class B (workflows content to `runtime`) against live source files and tests.\n","additions":6,"deletions":4},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,25 +1,51 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\",\n     \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n     \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n     \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n     \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n   ],\n-  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n-  \"keyFindings\": [],\n-  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"question\": \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes, if runtime is kept as non-routable infrastructure under the hub and the unified skill has exactly one graph-metadata identity.\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\n+      \"title\": \"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\n+      \"title\": \"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:16\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:101\"]\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Make runtime a mode packet\",\n+      \"reason\": \"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 0,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 0,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 2,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.2,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\": 4,\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\": 3,\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json\": 2\n+    }\n   }\n }\n","additions":36,"deletions":10}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-001.md\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-referen