rch\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:03:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n-- [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n+- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n@@\n - The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n+- The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n@@\n - Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n+- Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n@@\n - Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n+- The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n@@\n - Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n+- Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n@@\n-`system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow: verify the four planned path repairs and look for hidden dependency seams beyond package/typecheck/test-council wiring.\n+External reference migration completeness: validate commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, graph metadata edges, and worked examples.\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n     \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n     \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n   ],\n@@\n     {\n       \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n       \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n     }\n   ],\n@@\n     {\n       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\n       \"title\": \"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\n       \"summary\": \"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\",\n       \"sources\": [\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\n+      \"title\": \"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\n+      \"summary\": \"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\n+      \"title\": \"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"]\n     }\n   ],\n@@\n     {\n       \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\n       \"reason\": \"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, generated contract inputs, and historical/prose text.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Path repair is needed now; full compiler dependency decoupling is separate hardening and would conflate validation failures.\"\n     }\n   ],\n@@\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 5,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.4,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 7,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.6,\n@@\n-      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1,\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs\": 1,\n+      \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts\": 3\n     }\n   }\n }\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,43 @@\n+# Iteration 3: System-Spec-Kit Tooling Borrow And Hidden Seams\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Verify whether the child 002 plan's four `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repairs are complete enough for the post-move validation gates.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. **The four planned tooling-borrow edits are necessary and correctly scoped into phase 002.** `runtime/package.json` borrows `tsc` through `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc`, `runtime/tsconfig.json` points `typeRoots` at `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types`, `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json` runs two runtime council tests through `../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/...`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*`. After the runtime nests one level deeper, these paths must move exactly as the plan states. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18]\n+2. **Correction: `artifact-root.cjs` is a load-bearing hidden system-spec-kit seam omitted from the four-file list.** It re-exports `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` through a depth-sensitive relative path. After moving from `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` to `system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/`, the path needs one additional `..`; otherwise research/review reducers that import runtime's `artifact-root.cjs` fail at runtime. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:4] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:15]\n+3. **Correction: `artifact-root.vitest.ts` must move with the seam.** The test compares runtime's re-export with the original `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` through `../../../system-spec-kit/...`; after nesting it also needs one more hop. Without this, the runtime suite fails before it can validate the seam. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10]\n+4. **Correction: `test:council`'s own included `council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts` contains hardcoded deep-loop-runtime paths and regexes.** Because `test:council` explicitly includes this file, merely updating the package script's two runtime integration paths is not enough for the phase 002 `test:council` gate. The test's `DEEP_LOOP_RUNTIME_TEST_ROOT`, regexes, and resolver branch must recognize `system-deep-loop/runtime/tests`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:10] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:64]\n+5. **The plan's decision to fix paths without fully decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit remains reasonable.** The runtime has a self-containment guard that rejects production `lib/` and `scripts/` reach-ins to `system-spec-kit/**/node_modules`; it permits matching pinned dependency versions and does not require the package-level typecheck borrow to be removed now. Decoupling the compiler/typeRoots would be a separate behavior/tooling change. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts:1] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts:66]\n+6. **Additional system-spec-kit references belong in child 003 unless their tests are part of phase 002 gates.** `memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts` imports `../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.js`, and `scripts/tests/deep-review-auto-restart-contract.vitest.ts` reads the old `fanout-run.cjs` path. These are external reference migration work unless 002 chooses to run the full system-spec-kit suite before 003. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts:9] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-review-auto-restart-contract.vitest.ts:19]\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-review-auto-restart-contract.vitest.ts`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- `newInfoRatio`: 0.80\n+- Novelty justification: This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: `artifact-root` and a `test:council`-included path-integrity test.\n+- Confidence: High that `artifact-root.cjs` and its test are required; high that `council-playbook-anchor-integrity` affects `test:council`; medium on whether `memory-runtime-retention` must be phase 002 or child 003 because that depends on the chosen verification gate breadth.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: Following the validation command itself exposed test files that are semantically part of the borrow gate even though they live outside the four-file table.\n+- Failed: The phrase \"tooling-borrow\" was too narrow; the actual seam includes both compiler/test wiring and runtime's artifact-root re-export of a system-spec-kit shared resolver.\n+- Ruled out: Fully decoupling `runtime/` from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling in this merge; existing self-containment tests show production runtime dependencies are already local, and compiler decoupling is a separate hardening concern.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Validate external reference migration completeness across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, and graph metadata edges.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: artifact-root and a test:council-included path-integrity test.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:03:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T00:00:00Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and identity model\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.9,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass; most findings are new to this lineage and answer the structural identity question.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make runtime a mode packet\",\"reason\":\"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:95\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\"title\":\"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\"summary\":\"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\"title\":\"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\"summary\":\"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:5\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:4\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:01:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"The main rules were expected, but this pass found a concrete missing internal executable path and a broader runtime-test inventory.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\"reason\":\"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, and historical/prose text; each category needs separate handling.\",\"evidence\":\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\"title\":\"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\"summary\":\"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\"title\":\"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\"summary\":\"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\"title\":\"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\"summary\":\"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs:18\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:02:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: artifact-root and a test:council-included path-integrity test.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:03:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -15,27 +15,30 @@\n ## Key Questions\n \n - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n - [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n-- [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n+- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n - [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n - `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n - The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n+- The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n - Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n - Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n+- Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n - No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n - Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n+- The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n \n ## Exhausted Approaches\n \n - None yet.\n@@ -44,8 +47,9 @@\n \n - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n - Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n - Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n+- Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n \n ## Non-Goals\n \n - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n@@ -56,5 +60,5 @@\n - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-`system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow: verify the four planned path repairs and look for hidden dependency seams beyond package/typecheck/test-council wiring.\n+External reference migration completeness: validate commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, graph metadata edges, and worked examples.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,7 +1,6 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n     \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n     \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n   ],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n@@ -11,8 +10,12 @@\n     },\n     {\n       \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n       \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n     }\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\n@@ -43,8 +46,20 @@\n       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\n       \"title\": \"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\n       \"summary\": \"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\",\n       \"sources\": [\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\n+      \"title\": \"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\n+      \"summary\": \"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\n+      \"title\": \"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\n@@ -53,27 +68,33 @@\n     },\n     {\n       \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\n       \"reason\": \"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, generated contract inputs, and historical/prose text.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Path repair is needed now; full compiler dependency decoupling is separate hardening and would conflate validation failures.\"\n     }\n   ],\n   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 5,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.4,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 7,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.6,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\": 4,\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\": 3,\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json\": 2,\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs\": 1,\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs\": 2,\n-      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1,\n+      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs\": 1,\n+      \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts\": 3\n     }\n   }\n }\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/iterations/iteration-003.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,43 @@\n+# Iteration 3: System-Spec-Kit Tooling Borrow And Hidden Seams\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Verify whether the child 002 plan's four `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repairs are complete enough for the post-move validation gates.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. **The four planned tooling-borrow edits are necessary and correctly scoped into phase 002.** `runtime/package.json` borrows `tsc` through `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc`, `runtime/tsconfig.json` points `typeRoots` at `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types`, `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json` runs two runtime council tests through `../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/...`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*`. After the runtime nests one level deeper, these paths must move exactly as the plan states. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18]\n+2. **Correction: `artifact-root.cjs` is a load-bearing hidden system-spec-kit seam omitted from the four-file list.** It re-exports `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` through a depth-sensitive relative path. After moving from `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` to `system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/`, the path needs one additional `..`; otherwise research/review reducers that import runtime's `artifact-root.cjs` fail at runtime. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:4] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:15]\n+3. **Correction: `artifact-root.vitest.ts` must move with the seam.** The test compares runtime's re-export with the original `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` through `../../../system-spec-kit/...`; after nesting it also needs one more hop. Without this, the runtime suite fails before it can validate the seam. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10]\n+4. **Correction: `test:council`'s own included `council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts` contains hardcoded deep-loop-runtime paths and regexes.** Because `test:council` explicitly includes this file, merely updating the package script's two runtime integration paths is not enough for the phase 002 `test:council` gate. The test's `DEEP_LOOP_RUNTIME_TEST_ROOT`, regexes, and resolver branch must recognize `system-deep-loop/runtime/tests`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:10] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:64]\n+5. **The plan's decision to fix paths without fully decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit remains reasonable.** The runtime has a self-containment guard that rejects production `lib/` and `scripts/` reach-ins to `system-spec-kit/**/node_modules`; it permits matching pinned dependency versions and does not require the package-level typecheck borrow to be removed now. Decoupling the compiler/typeRoots would be a separate behavior/tooling change. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts:1] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts:66]\n+6. **Additional system-spec-kit references belong in child 003 unless their tests are part of phase 002 gates.** `memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts` imports `../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.js`, and `scripts/tests/deep-review-auto-restart-contract.vitest.ts` reads the old `fanout-run.cjs` path. These are external reference migration work unless 002 chooses to run the full system-spec-kit suite before 003. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts:9] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-review-auto-restart-contract.vitest.ts:19]\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-review-auto-restart-contract.vitest.ts`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- `newInfoRatio`: 0.80\n+- Novelty justification: This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: `artifact-root` and a `test:council`-included path-integrity test.\n+- Confidence: High that `artifact-root.cjs` and its test are required; high that `council-playbook-anchor-integrity` affects `test:council`; medium on whether `memory-runtime-retention` must be phase 002 or child 003 because that depends on the chosen verification gate breadth.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: Following the validation command itself exposed test files that are semantically part of the borrow gate even though they live outside the four-file table.\n+- Failed: The phrase \"tooling-borrow\" was too narrow; the actual seam includes both compiler/test wiring and runtime's artifact-root re-export of a system-spec-kit shared resolver.\n+- Ruled out: Fully decoupling `runtime/` from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling in this merge; existing self-containment tests show production runtime dependencies are already local, and compiler decoupling is a separate hardening concern.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Validate external reference migration completeness across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, and graph metadata edges.\n","additions":43,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: artifact-root and a test:council-included path-integrity test.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:03:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T00:00:00Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and identity model\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.9,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass; most findings are new to this lineage and answer the structural identity question.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make runtime a mode packet\",\"reason\":\"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:95\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\"title\":\"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\"summary\":\"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\"title\":\"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\"summary\":\"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:5\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:4\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:01:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"The main rules were expected, but this pass found a concrete missing internal executable path and a broader runtime-test inventory.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\"reason\":\"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, and historical/prose text; each category needs separate handling.\",\"evidence\":\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\"title\":\"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\"summary\":\"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\"title\":\"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\"summary\":\"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\"title\":\"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\"summary\":\"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs:18\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:02:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: artifact-root and a test:council-included path-integrity test.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:03:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -15,27 +15,30 @@\n ## Key Questions\n \n - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n - [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n-- [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n+- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n - [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n - `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n - The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n+- The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n - Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n - Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n+- Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n - No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n - Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n+- The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n \n ## Exhausted Approaches\n \n - None yet.\n@@ -44,8 +47,9 @@\n \n - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n - Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n - Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n+- Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n \n ## Non-Goals\n \n - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n@@ -56,5 +60,5 @@\n - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-`system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow: verify the four planned path repairs and look for hidden dependency seams beyond package/typecheck/test-council wiring.\n+External reference migration completeness: validate commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, graph metadata edges, and worked examples.\n","additions":6,"deletions":2},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,7 +1,6 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n     \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n     \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n   ],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n@@ -11,8 +10,12 @@\n     },\n     {\n       \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n       \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n     }\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\n@@ -43,8 +46,20 @@\n       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\n       \"title\": \"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\n       \"summary\": \"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\",\n       \"sources\": [\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\n+      \"title\": \"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\n+      \"summary\": \"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\n+      \"title\": \"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\n@@ -53,27 +68,33 @@\n     },\n     {\n       \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\n       \"reason\": \"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, generated contract inputs, and historical/prose text.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Decouple runtime fro