/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, `.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml`, `sk-code/assets/scripts/verify_stack_folders.py`. Edited: `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit`, `deep-improvement/scripts/lib/mirror-sync-verify.cjs` (normalizer), `.codex/agents/context.toml` (drift fix). Verification: run the gate, the stack-folders check, the pre-commit hook (throwaway index), a normalizer tamper control.\n\n  Line 72: `node --check`; `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs --all` → exit 0 (all 12 in-sync); `verify_stack_folders.py` → exit 0; pre-commit hook tested via a throwaway `GIT_INDEX_FILE` (clean→0, drifted→1, real index unchanged); a normalizer tamper control (a genuine extra word still yields drift); comment-hygiene on the new `.cjs`/`.py`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/z_archive/015-sk-code-ponytail-based-refinement/004-mirror-stackfolder-drift-guards/tasks.md:\n  Line 43: - [x] T-003 `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` (changed paths or --all; per-runtime drift output; exit 1 on drift).\n\n  Line 56: - [x] T-009 `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs --all` → all 12 in-sync, exit 0.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/z_archive/015-sk-code-ponytail-based-refinement/004-mirror-stackfolder-drift-guards/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 41: - **`deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`** — a repo-wide executable wrapping the existing `verifyMirrorSync` lib. Takes changed agent paths or `--all`; reports per-runtime drift; exit 1 on any drift.\n\n  Line 75: - `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs --all` → **12 agents checked, all mirrors in sync, exit 0** (orchestrator-run).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:\n  Line 20: Every agent is authored once under `.opencode/agents/<name>.md` and mirrored to `.claude/agents/<name>.md` and `.codex/agents/<name>.toml` so each runtime ships the same behavior. Editing one copy without the others makes the runtimes silently disagree. A new `scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` wraps the existing `verifyMirrorSync` library and turns it into a gate: given the changed agent files (or `--all`), it fails when any agent's mirrors drift from its `.opencode` canonical body — including a deleted mirror, or a deleted canonical whose runtime copies still linger. It is wired changed-files-scoped over added, modified, and deleted agent paths into `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` and into a new `.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml` that fails closed if the checker is ever removed, so the divergence is caught at commit and pull-request time instead of in production. This promotes the mirror check from a deep-improvement promotion-only gate to an every-commit and every-PR gate.\n\n  Line 38: - `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` — new changed-files-scoped (or `--all`) gate wrapping `verifyMirrorSync`.\n\n  Line 49: No migration required. The gate is additive — it runs against changed agent files at commit time and against the full set in CI, and it only fails when a mirror genuinely diverges from its `.opencode` canonical. Run `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs --all` to verify all mirrors locally.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/z_archive/015-sk-code-ponytail-based-refinement/changelog/changelog-142-004-mirror-stackfolder-drift-guards.md:\n  Line 36: - T-003 added `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` with changed paths or `--all`, per-runtime drift output and exit 1 on drift.\n\n  Line 63: | `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` | Created | Added changed-file-aware agent mirror drift checker |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:\n  Line 3: // ║ check-agent-mirror-sync — block agent edits that desync runtime mirrors  ║\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/z_archive/015-sk-code-ponytail-based-refinement/changelog/changelog-142-root.md:\n  Line 44: - `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, the `agent-mirror-sync.yml` workflow and `verify_stack_folders.py`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/z_archive/015-sk-code-ponytail-based-refinement/review/review-report.md:\n  Line 11: **Scope reviewed:** the uncommitted packet-146 footprint — new guard scripts (`check-rule-copies.js`, `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, `verify_stack_folders.py` + a test), the `mirror-sync-verify.cjs` normalizer change, two CI workflows, the `pre-commit` edit, the `.codex/agents/context.toml` fix, the doc/rule additions to sk-code + sk-code-review, and the 3 changelogs + 3 README edits.\n\n  Line 35: | 6 | `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` treats a **missing `.opencode` canonical as \"in sync\"** — an orphan/stale runtime mirror reads green (probe confirmed). | `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:58-62` | Fail when a changed agent path has no canonical, or check mirror existence. |\n\n  Line 78: | 6 | P2 | `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` flags an orphan canonical whose mirrors linger | FIXED |\n\n  Line 86: Verification: `check-rule-copies.js` exit 0 + self-test 3/3; `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs --all` 12/12; `verify_stack_folders.py` exit 0; `mirror-sync-verify.vitest.ts` 3/3; comment-hygiene clean on all changed assets.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/README.md:\n  Line 81: An agent is more than its `.md` file. `scan-integration.cjs` inventories the canonical agent definition (`.opencode/agents/`), its Claude runtime mirror (`.claude/agents/`), command dispatch files, YAML workflow assets, skill references and the skill-advisor routing path. The scanner extracts emphasized strings from the canonical agent and marks a mirror aligned when enough of them appear. A drifted mirror shows up before it causes a runtime surprise, and the score reflects the whole integration surface, not the prompt in isolation. Mirror parity is also enforced repo-wide outside a scoring run: `scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` gates commits (through `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit`) and pull requests into `main` (through `.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml`), so drifted runtime copies are caught before they merge. The commit hook fails open when Node or the checker is unavailable so it never blocks an unrelated commit; the CI gate on `main` is the fail-closed backstop.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/119-parent-skill-native-invocability/001-native-invocability-planning/review/iterations/iteration-010.md:\n  Line 3591: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:10:// fails when any agent's mirrors drift from its .opencode canonical body, so the\n\n  Line 3592: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:71:  const drifted = [];\n\n  Line 3593: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:85:        drifted.push(name);\n\n  Line 3594: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:100:      drifted.push(name);\n\n  Line 3595: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:109:    drifted.push(name);\n\n  Line 3596: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:111:      if (detail.status === 'missing') {\n\n  Line 3597: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs:113:      } else if (detail.status === 'drift') {\n\n  Line 