w paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T00:00:00Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and identity model\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.9,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass; most findings are new to this lineage and answer the structural identity question.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make runtime a mode packet\",\"reason\":\"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:95\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\"title\":\"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\"summary\":\"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\"title\":\"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\"summary\":\"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:5\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:4\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:01:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"The main rules were expected, but this pass found a concrete missing internal executable path and a broader runtime-test inventory.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\"reason\":\"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, and historical/prose text; each category needs separate handling.\",\"evidence\":\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\"title\":\"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\"summary\":\"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\"title\":\"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\"summary\":\"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\"title\":\"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\"summary\":\"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs:18\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"r... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: artifact-root and a test:council-included path-integrity test.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":4,"totalLines":4,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1783487333752,"end":1783487333799}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c14f2b509f02880016a4ddb65af8c81919c52e694cd4f4317"}},"id":"prt_f40210574001NcCVxrX8fiA05Q","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f4020dfd4001cpKljJLTCHxBz8"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487333803,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_RYFeTUfa1E3kfOVD2XEemiLw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy\n2: \n3: ## Research Topic\n4: \n5: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n6: \n7: ## Known Context\n8: \n9: - Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n10: - Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n11: - `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n12: - This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n13: - Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n14: \n15: ## Key Questions\n16: \n17: - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n18: - [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n19: - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n20: - [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n21: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n22: \n23: ## Answered Questions\n24: \n25: - `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n26: - The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n27: - The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n28: \n29: ## What Worked\n30: \n31: - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n32: - Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n33: - Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n34: - Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n35: \n36: ## What Failed\n37: \n38: - No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n39: - Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n40: - The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n41: \n42: ## Exhausted Approaches\n43: \n44: - None yet.\n45: \n46: ## Ruled-Out Directions\n47: \n48: - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n49: - Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n50: - Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n51: - Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n52: \n53: ## Non-Goals\n54: \n55: - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n56: - Do not rename `/deep:*` commands or agent names as part of the recommendation unless evidence shows a blocking contradiction.\n57: \n58: ## Stop Conditions\n59: \n60: - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n61: \n62: ## Next Focus\n63: \n64: External reference migration completeness: validate commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, graph metadata edges, and worked examples.\n\n(End of file - total 64 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n- Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n- [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n- [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n- Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n- [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n- [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n\n## Answered Questions\n\n- `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n- The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n- The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n- Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n- Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n- Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n\n## What Failed\n\n- No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n- Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n- The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n- None yet.\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n- Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n- Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n- Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n- Do not rename `/deep:*` commands or agent names as part of the recommendation unless evidence shows a blocking contradiction.\n\n## Stop Conditions\n\n- Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nExternal reference migration completeness: validate commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, graph metadata edges, and worked examples.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":64,"totalLines":64,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783487333760,"end":1783487333801}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c14f2b509f02880016a4ddb65af9481919bea9cdaf65eab7c"}},"id":"prt_f4021057b001YklYUiLPeymUjL","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f4020dfd4001cpKljJLTCHxBz8"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487333807,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_RdGT2a2lN0i9CpK9m5iW7pE2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"openQuestions\": [\n3:     \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n4:     \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n5:   ],\n6:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n7:     {\n8:       \"question\": \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\",\n9:       \"answer\": \"Yes, if runtime is kept as non-routable infrastructure under the hub and the unified skill has exactly one graph-metadata identity.\"\n10:     },\n11:     {\n12:       \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n13:       \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n14:     },\n15:     {\n16:       \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n17:       \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n18:     }\n19:   ],\n20:   \"keyFindings\": [\n21:     {\n22:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\n23:       \"title\": \"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n24:       \"summary\": \"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\",\n25:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]\n26:     },\n27:     {\n28:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\n29:       \"title\": \"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\n30:       \"summary\": \"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\",\n31:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:16\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:101\"]\n32:     },\n33:     {\n34:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\n35:       \"title\": \"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\n36:       \"summary\": \"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\",\n37:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\"]\n38:     },\n39:     {\n40:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\n41:       \"title\": \"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\n42:       \"summary\": \"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\",\n43:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:51\"]\n44:     },\n45:     {\n46:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\n47:       \"title\": \"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\n48:       \"summary\": \"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\",\n49:       \"sources\": [\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"]\n50:     },\n51:     {\n52:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\n53:       \"title\": \"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\n54:       \"summary\": \"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\",\n55:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\"]\n56:     },\n57:     {\n58:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\n59:       \"title\": \"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\n60:       \"summary\": \"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\",\n61:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"]\n62:     }\n63:   ],\n64:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n65:     {\n66:       \"approach\": \"Make runtime a mode packet\",\n67:       \"reason\": \"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\"\n68:     },\n69:     {\n70:       \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\n71:       \"reason\": \"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, generated contract inputs, and historical/prose text.\"\n72:     },\n73:     {\n74:       \"approach\": \"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\n75:       \"reason\": \"Path repair is needed now; full compiler dependency decoupling is separate hardening and would conflate validation failures.\"\n76:     }\n77:   ],\n78:   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n79:   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n80:   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n81:   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n82:   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n83:   \"metrics\": {\n84:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n85:     \"openQuestions\": 2,\n86:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n87:     \"keyFindings\": 7,\n88:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.6,\n89:     \"coverageBySources\": {\n90:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\": 4,\n91:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\": 3,\n92:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json\": 2,\n93:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs\": 1,\n94:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs\": 2,\n95:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1,\n96:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs\": 1,\n97:       \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts\": 3\n98:     }\n99:   }\n100: }\n\n(End of file - total 100 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n    \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\",\n      \"answer\": \"Yes, if runtime is kept as non-routable infrastructure under the hub and the unified skill has exactly one graph-metadata identity.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n      \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n      \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n    \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\",\n      \"answer\": \"Yes, if runtime is kept as non-routable infrastructure under the hub and the unified skill has exactly one graph-metadata identity.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n      \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n      \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\n      \"title\": \"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n      \"summary\": \"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\n      \"title\": \"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\n      \"summary\": \"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:16\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:101\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\n      \"title\": \"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\n      \"summary\": \"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop cou