 {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and identity model\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.9,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass; most findings are new to this lineage and answer the structural identity question.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make runtime a mode packet\",\"reason\":\"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:95\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\"title\":\"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\"summary\":\"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\"title\":\"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\"summary\":\"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:5\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:4\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:01:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"The main rules were expected, but this pass found a concrete missing internal executable path and a broader runtime-test inventory.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\"reason\":\"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, and historical/prose text; each category needs separate handling.\",\"evidence\":\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\"title\":\"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\"summary\":\"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\"title\":\"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\"summary\":\"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\"title\":\"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\"summary\":\"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs:18\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:02:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass confirms the four listed borrow edits but adds two phase-002-blocking omissions: artifact-root and a test:council-included path-integrity test.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\"reason\":\"The merge can repair path depth only; decoupling compiler dependencies is separate hardening and would conflate failure modes.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:99\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\"title\":\"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\"summary\":\"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\"title\":\"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\"summary\":\"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:03:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"run\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"External reference migration completeness\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"The broad category plan was expected, but this pass corrected stale assumptions, confirmed current advisor/scorer paths, and found a duplicate graph-edge cleanup detail.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Hand-edit compiled command contracts\",\"reason\":\"The compiled contract header identifies compile-command-contracts.cjs as the generator; source assets and router files must be edited then regenerated.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:6\"}],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f008\",\"title\":\"External migration plan is directionally complete and category-driven\",\"summary\":\"The 003 plan covers hardcoded constants, structured identity fields, codegen, command assets, docs, graph metadata, examples, advisor corpus, and final verification as separate categories.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f009\",\"title\":\"Advisor projection migration must be synchronized\",\"summary\":\"Python, TypeScript scorer files, and the drift guard all hardcode the merged deep skill identity and registry/projection contract.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f010\",\"title\":\"Hook, CI, plugin, and doctor surfaces are live migration targets\",\"summary\":\"The mirror checker, GitHub workflow, loop guard, and parent-skill doctor checker all contain old deep-loop paths or assumptions.\"},{\"id\":\"gpt55-fast-6-f011\",\"title\":\"Sibling graph migration should dedupe duplicate cli-opencode edges\",\"summary\":\"The migration should preserve meaningful contextual edges while collapsing literal duplicate targets.\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\",\"file:.opencode/hooks/pre-commit:40\",\"file:.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/graph-metadata.json:31\"],\"route_proof\":{\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"},\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:04:00Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-6-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -16,29 +16,32 @@\n \n - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n - [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n-- [ ] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n+- [x] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n - `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n - The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n - The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n+- The external reference migration plan is directionally complete across the major live surfaces; keep its staged category model, synchronize advisor projection/codegen/drift guards, regenerate compiled command contracts, and explicitly dedupe duplicate graph edges such as `cli-opencode`.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n - Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n - Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n - Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n+- Current-file verification prevented stale-gaps from being carried forward; the 003 plan already includes `sk-prompt`, pre-commit/GitHub Actions mirror paths, and advisor codegen staging.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n - No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n - Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n - The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n+- External reference inventory alone does not prove plan gaps; generated outputs, live source assets, routing fixtures, and historical docs need category-specific decisions.\n \n ## Exhausted Approaches\n \n - None yet.\n@@ -48,8 +51,9 @@\n - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n - Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n - Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n - Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n+- Hand-editing compiled command contracts is ruled out; update source command assets/router files and rerun contract compilation.\n \n ## Non-Goals\n \n - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n@@ -60,5 +64,5 @@\n - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-External reference migration completeness: validate commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, generated contracts, graph metadata edges, and worked examples.\n+Fallback-router real wiring decision: inspect `fallback-router.ts`, its tests, and `fanout-run.cjs` retry/failure paths, then decide whether GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback should land now or remain optional.\n","additions":6,"deletions":2},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/s