 them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 147: > **Feature File:** [DLR-003](01--executor/fallback-router.md)\n\n  Line 162: > **Feature File:** [DLR-044](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md)\n\n  Line 852: | Executor | `tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/executor-audit*.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/cli-matrix.vitest.ts` | Executor parsing, audit, fallback, and CLI dispatch behavior. |\n\n  Line 871: | DLR-003 | [F003 Fallback router](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router.md](01--executor/fallback-router.md) |\n\n  Line 912: | DLR-044 | [F042 Fallback-router typed reroute](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-r