{"type":"text","timestamp":1783487622190,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"id":"prt_f402559be001VtOjjp5ZPT40sX","messageID":"msg_f40254971001h40TnOofSDUzcL","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","type":"text","text":"`fanout-run.cjs` confirms the runner has the lineage model/kind context and failure classifications, while `fanout-pool.cjs` only sees generic items and retry counters. That shifts the safer design from “wire router into pool” toward “wire model fallback in the fanout runner or pass an explicit pool hook.”","time":{"start":1783487617470,"end":1783487622188},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0de149b52702f4dc016a4ddc8173088191aed5ea59b5a7535b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487622228,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_K1ptHF0avYmYwkeyuM0rQzeQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"function parseFanoutConfig|export function parseFanoutConfig|interface Fanout|fallback|modelRegistry|maxRetries|executors","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop","include":"executor-config.ts"},"output":"Found 9 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:\n  Line 273:   executors: z.array(lineageExecutorSchema).min(1),\n\n  Line 276:   maxRetries: z.number().int().nonnegative().default(5),\n\n  Line 297: export function parseFanoutConfig(raw: unknown): FanoutConfig {\n\n  Line 306:   config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n\n  Line 322:           issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['executors', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n\n  Line 331:   config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n\n  Line 334:         issues: [{ path: ['executors', index, 'label'], message: `duplicate lineage label '${entry.label}'` }],\n\n  Line 345:         issues: [{ path: ['executors'], message: `expanded lineage label '${lineage.label}' collides; rename base labels` }],\n\n  Line 366:   for (const entry of config.executors) {\n","metadata":{"matches":9,"truncated":false},"title":"function parseFanoutConfig|export function parseFanoutConfig|interface Fanout|fallback|modelRegistry|maxRetries|executors","time":{"start":1783487622217,"end":1783487622228}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0de149b52702f4dc016a4ddc8626888191bce6afd5b3216b60"}},"id":"prt_f40256c2d001JDq7dRJ945fN2V","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40254971001h40TnOofSDUzcL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487622250,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_nuPUyPXEP93gpXXpcpZIgt2Q","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Deep-Loop Executor Config\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: \n5: import { z } from 'zod';\n6: \n7: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8: // 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n9: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10: \n11: export const EXECUTOR_KINDS = ['native', 'cli-claude-code', 'cli-opencode'] as const;\n12: export type ExecutorKind = typeof EXECUTOR_KINDS[number];\n13: \n14: export const REASONING_EFFORTS = ['none', 'minimal', 'low', 'medium', 'high', 'xhigh', 'max'] as const;\n15: export type ReasoningEffort = typeof REASONING_EFFORTS[number];\n16: \n17: export const SERVICE_TIERS = ['priority', 'standard', 'fast'] as const;\n18: export type ServiceTier = typeof SERVICE_TIERS[number];\n19: \n20: /** Fan-out assignment models accepted by the schema. */\n21: export const FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS = ['flat_pool', 'wave'] as const;\n22: \n23: /** Fan-out assignment model selected for a lineage or fan-out block. */\n24: export type FanoutAssignmentModel = typeof FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS[number];\n25: \n26: const SANDBOX_MODES = ['read-only', 'workspace-write', 'danger-full-access'] as const;\n27: export type SandboxMode = typeof SANDBOX_MODES[number];\n28: export type ClaudePermissionMode = 'plan' | 'acceptEdits' | 'bypassPermissions';\n29: \n30: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n31: // 2. CONSTANTS\n32: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n33: \n34: export const executorConfigSchema = z.object({\n35:   kind: z.enum(EXECUTOR_KINDS).default('native'),\n36:   model: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n37:   configDir: z.string().trim().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n38:   reasoningEffort: z.enum(REASONING_EFFORTS).nullable().default(null),\n39:   serviceTier: z.enum(SERVICE_TIERS).nullable().default(null),\n40:   sandboxMode: z.enum(SANDBOX_MODES).nullable().default(null),\n41:   timeoutSeconds: z.number().int().positive().default(900),\n42:   // Optional fable-5 governor capsule for this executor's prompts. Universal and\n43:   // kind-agnostic on purpose: intentionally absent from EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT\n44:   // and the unsupported-field scan, so any executor kind may carry it. null = none.\n45:   governor: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n46: });\n47: \n48: export type ExecutorConfig = z.infer<typeof executorConfigSchema>;\n49: \n50: export const EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT: Record<ExecutorKind, readonly (keyof ExecutorConfig)[]> = {\n51:   native: [],\n52:   'cli-claude-code': ['model', 'configDir', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds'],\n53:   'cli-opencode': ['model', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds'],\n54: };\n55: \n56: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n57: // 3. DOMAIN ERRORS\n58: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n59: \n60: type ExecutorConfigIssue = {\n61:   path: PropertyKey[];\n62:   message: string;\n63: };\n64: \n65: /** Error thrown when a reserved executor kind is selected before wiring exists. */\n66: export class ExecutorNotWiredError extends Error {\n67:   kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>;\n68: \n69:   constructor(kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>) {\n70:     super(`Executor kind '${kind}' is reserved in the schema but not yet wired. Awaiting future spec for ${kind} integration.`);\n71:     this.name = 'ExecutorNotWiredError';\n72:     this.kind = kind;\n73:   }\n74: }\n75: \n76: /** Error thrown when executor configuration validation fails. */\n77: export class ExecutorConfigError extends Error {\n78:   issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[];\n79: \n80:   constructor(input: { issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[] }) {\n81:     super(input.issues.map((issue) => `${issue.path.map(String).join('.') || '<root>'}: ${issue.message}`).join('; '));\n82:     this.name = 'ExecutorConfigError';\n83:     this.issues = input.issues;\n84:   }\n85: }\n86: \n87: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n88: // 4. HELPERS\n89: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n90: \n91: function isRecord(value: unknown): value is Record<string, unknown> {\n92:   return value !== null && !Array.isArray(value) && typeof value === 'object';\n93: }\n94: \n95: function normalizeSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n96:   return mode ?? 'workspace-write';\n97: }\n98: \n99: function normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw: unknown): unknown {\n100:   if (!isRecord(raw) || !Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'type')) {\n101:     return raw;\n102:   }\n103: \n104:   const legacyKind = raw.type;\n105:   if (typeof legacyKind !== 'string') {\n106:     return raw;\n107:   }\n108: \n109:   if (typeof raw.kind === 'string' && raw.kind !== legacyKind) {\n110:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n111:       issues: [{\n112:         path: ['type'],\n113:         message: `deprecated executor field 'type' conflicts with canonical kind '${raw.kind}'`,\n114:       }],\n115:     });\n116:   }\n117: \n118:   console.warn(\"[executor-config] Deprecated executor field 'type' was provided; use 'kind' instead.\");\n119:   const { type: _legacyType, ...rest } = raw;\n120:   return {\n121:     ...rest,\n122:     kind: typeof raw.kind === 'string' ? raw.kind : legacyKind,\n123:   };\n124: }\n125: \n126: function normalizeIssues(error: z.ZodError<ExecutorConfig>): ExecutorConfigIssue[] {\n127:   return error.issues.map((issue) => ({\n128:     path: issue.path,\n129:     message: issue.message,\n130:   }));\n131: }\n132: \n133: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n134: // 5. EXPORTS\n135: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n136: \n137: /**\n138:  * Map a generic sandbox mode to the executor-agnostic CLI sandbox mode.\n139:  *\n140:  * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n141:  * @returns CLI-compatible sandbox mode.\n142:  */\n143: export function resolveSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n144:   return normalizeSandboxMode(mode);\n145: }\n146: \n147: /**\n148:  * Map a generic sandbox mode to the Claude Code permission mode.\n149:  *\n150:  * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n151:  * @returns Claude-compatible permission mode.\n152:  */\n153: export function resolveClaudePermissionMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): ClaudePermissionMode {\n154:   switch (normalizeSandboxMode(mode)) {\n155:     case 'read-only':\n156:       return 'plan';\n157:     case 'danger-full-access':\n158:       return 'bypassPermissions';\n159:     default:\n160:       return 'acceptEdits';\n161:   }\n162: }\n163: \n164: /**\n165:  * Parse and validate a raw executor configuration.\n166:  *\n167:  * Normalizes legacy `type` fields, validates against the Zod schema,\n168:  * and enforces executor-kind-specific field support.\n169:  *\n170:  * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n171:  * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n172:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n173:  */\n174: export function parseExecutorConfig(raw: unknown): ExecutorConfig {\n175:   const parsed = executorConfigSchema.safeParse(normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw));\n176:   if (!parsed.success) {\n177:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n178:       issues: normalizeIssues(parsed.error),\n179:     });\n180:   }\n181: \n182:   const config = parsed.data;\n183:   const supportedFlags = EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT[config.kind];\n184:   const unsupportedFields: string[] = [];\n185:   const allOptionalFields: (keyof ExecutorConfig)[] = [\n186:     'model',\n187:     'configDir',\n188:     'reasoningEffort',\n189:     'serviceTier',\n190:     'sandboxMode',\n191:     'timeoutSeconds',\n192:   ];\n193: \n194:   for (const field of allOptionalFields) {\n195:     if (!supportedFlags.includes(field) && config[field] !== null && !(field === 'timeoutSeconds' && config[field] === 900)) {\n196:       unsupportedFields.push(field);\n197:     }\n198:   }\n199: \n200:   if (unsupportedFields.length > 0) {\n201:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n202:       issues: unsupportedFields.map((field) => ({\n203:         path: [field],\n204:         message: `field '${field}' is not supported by executor kind '${config.kind}'. Supported fields for ${config.kind}: ${\n205:           supportedFlags.length ? supportedFlags.join(', ') : 'none'\n206:         }.`,\n207:       })),\n208:     });\n209:   }\n210: \n211:   return config;\n212: }\n213: \n214: /**\n215:  * Resolve an executor configuration by merging CLI and file sources.\n216:  *\n217:  * @param sources - CLI and file partial configs (CLI takes precedence).\n218:  * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n219:  */\n220: export function resolveExecutorConfig(sources: {\n221:   cli?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n222:   file?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n223: }): ExecutorConfig {\n224:   const merged = {\n225:     ...(sources.file ?? {}),\n226:     ...(sources.cli ?? {}),\n227:   };\n228:   return parseExecutorConfig(merged);\n229: }\n230: \n231: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n232: // 6. FAN-OUT CONFIG\n233: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n234: //\n235: // Opt-in layer ABOVE the single-executor path. When a fan-out config is present,\n236: // the loop runs N executor \"lineages\" concurrently (capped), each running the\n237: // existing sequential loop in its own isolated sub-packet. The single-executor\n238: // path (executorConfigSchema / parseExecutorConfig) is untouched and remains the\n239: // default; callers use EITHER a single `executor` OR a `fanout` block, never both.\n240: \n241: const LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN = /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/;\n242: \n243: /**\n244:  * One fan-out lineage: a single executor config plus fan-out metadata.\n245:  *\n246:  * - `label`: directory-safe id for the lineage's isolated sub-packet.\n247:  * - `count`: number of replicas of THIS config to run (e.g. 5x the same model).\n248:  * - `iterations`: per-lineage max-iterations override; null = packet default.\n249:  * - `promptFramework`: optional per-model prompt framing key (e.g. \"costar\",\n250:  *   \"tidd-ec\") resolved against sk-prompt-models when a consumer renders the\n251:  *   lineage prompt. null = consumer default. Loop-type-agnostic and optional, so\n252:  *   research/review lineages that omit it are unaffected.\n253:  * - `assignment_model`: defaults to the existing flat pool; `wave` is accepted\n254:  *   only so the runtime guard can reject activation attempts explicitly.\n255:  * - `depends_on` / `touches`: reserved dependency and path-domain metadata for\n256:  *   a future guarded planner; flat-pool execution ignores them after logging.\n257:  */\n258: export const lineageExecutorSchema = executorConfigSchema.extend({\n259:   label: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n260:     message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 376. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Deep-Loop Executor Config\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { z } from 'zod';\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const EXECUTOR_KINDS = ['native', 'cli-claude-code', 'cli-opencode'] as const;\nexport type ExecutorKind = typeof EXECUTOR_KINDS[number];\n\nexport const REASONING_EFFORTS = ['none', 'minimal', 'low', 'medium', 'high', 'xhigh', 'max'] as const;\nexport type ReasoningEffort = typeof REASONING_EFFORTS[number];\n\nexport const SERVICE_TIERS = ['priority', 'standard', 'fast'] as const;\nexport type ServiceTier = typeof SERVICE_TIERS[number];\n\n/** Fan-out assignment models accepted by the schema. */","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Deep-Loop Executor Config\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { z } from 'zod';\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const EXECUTOR_KINDS = ['native', 'cli-claude-code', 'cli-opencode'] as const;\nexport type ExecutorKind = typeof EXECUTOR_KINDS[number];\n\nexport const REASONING_EFFORTS = ['none', 'minimal', 'low', 'medium', 'high', 'xhigh', 'max'] as const;\nexport type ReasoningEffort = typeof REASONING_EFFORTS[number];\n\nexport const SERVICE_TIERS = ['priority', 'standard', 'fast'] as const;\nexport type ServiceTier = typeof SERVICE_TIERS[number];\n\n/** Fan-out assignment models accepted by the schema. */\nexport const FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS = ['flat_pool', 'wave'] as const;\n\n/** Fan-out assignment model selected for a lineage or fan-out block. */\nexport type FanoutAssignmentModel = typeof FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS[number];\n\nconst SANDBOX_MODES = ['read-only', 'workspace-write', 'danger-full-access'] as const;\nexport type SandboxMode = typeof SANDBOX_MODES[number];\nexport type ClaudePermissionMode = 'plan' | 'acceptEdits' | 'bypassPermissions';\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const executorConfigSchema = z.object({\n  kind: z.enum(EXECUTOR_KINDS).default('native'),\n  model: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  configDir: z.string().trim().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  reasoningEffort: z.enum(REASONING_EFFORTS).nullable().default(null),\n  serviceTier: z.enum(SERVICE_TIERS).nullable().default(null),\n  sandboxMode: z.enum(SANDBOX_MODES).nullable().default(null),\n  timeoutSeconds: z.number().int().positive().default(900),\n  // Optional fable-5 governor capsule for this executor's prompts. Universal and\n  // kind-agnostic on purpose: intentionally absent from EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT\n  // and the unsupported-field scan, so any executor kind may carry it. null = none.\n  governor: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n});\n\nexport type ExecutorConfig = z.infer<typeof executorConfigSchema>;\n\nexport const EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT: Record<ExecutorKind, readonly (keyof ExecutorConfig)[]> = {\n  native: [],\n  'cli-claude-code': ['model', 'configDir', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds'],\n  'cli-opencode': ['model', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds'],\n};\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. DOMAIN ERRORS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ntype ExecutorConfigIssue = {\n  path: PropertyKey[];\n  message: string;\n};\n\n/** Error thrown when a reserved executor kind is selected before wiring exists. */\nexport class ExecutorNotWiredError extends Error {\n  kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>;\n\n  constructor(kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>) {\n    super(`Executor kind '${kind}' is reserved in the schema but not yet wired. Awaiting future spec for ${kind} integration.`);\n    this.name = 'ExecutorNotWiredError';\n    this.kind = kind;\n  }\n}\n\n/** Error thrown when executor configuration validation fails. */\nexport class ExecutorConfigError extends Error {\n  issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[];\n\n  constructor(input: { issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[] }) {\n    super(input.issues.map((issue) => `${issue.path.map(String).join('.') || '<root>'}: ${issue.message}`).join('; '));\n    this.name = 'ExecutorConfigError';\n    this.issues = input.issues;\n  }\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. HELPERS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction isRecord(value: unknown): value is Record<string, unknown> {\n  return value !== null && !Array.isArray(value) && typeof value === 'object';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n  return mode ?? 'workspace-write';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw: unknown): unknown {\n  if (!isRecord(raw) || !Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'type')) {\n    return raw;\n  }\n\n  const legacyKind = raw.type;\n  if (typeof legacyKind !== 'string') {\n    return raw;\n  }\n\n  if (typeof raw.kind === 'string' && raw.kind !== legacyKind) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: [{\n        path: ['type'],\n        message: `deprecated executor field 'type' conflicts with canonical kind '${raw.kind}'`,\n      }],\n    });\n  }\n\n  console.warn(\"[executor-config] Deprecated executor field 'type' was provided; use 'kind' instead.\");\n  const { type: _legacyType, ...rest } = raw;\n  return {\n    ...rest,\n    kind: typeof raw.kind === 'string' ? raw.kind : legacyKind,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction normalizeIssues(error: z.ZodError<ExecutorConfig>): ExecutorConfigIssue[] {\n  return error.issues.map((issue) => ({\n    path: issue.path,\n    message: issue.message,\n  }));\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 5. EXPORTS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Map a generic sandbox mode to the executor-agnostic CLI sandbox mode.\n *\n * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n * @returns CLI-compatible sandbox mode.\n */\nexport function resolveSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n  return normalizeSandboxMode(mode);\n}\n\n/**\n * Map a generic sandbox mode to the Claude Code permission mode.\n *\n * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n * @returns Claude-compatible permission mode.\n */\nexport function resolveClaudePermissionMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): ClaudePermissionMode {\n  switch (normalizeSandboxMode(mode)) {\n    case 'read-only':\n      return 'plan';\n    case 'danger-full-access':\n      return 'bypassPermissions';\n    default:\n      return 'acceptEdits';\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse and validate a raw executor configuration.\n *\n * Normalizes legacy `type` fields, validates against the Zod schema,\n * and enforces executor-kind-specific field support.\n *\n * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n */\nexport function parseExecutorConfig(raw: unknown): ExecutorConfig {\n  const parsed = executorConfigSchema.safeParse(normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw));\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: normalizeIssues(parsed.error),\n    });\n  }\n\n  const config = parsed.data;\n  const supportedFlags = EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT[config.kind];\n  const unsupportedFields: string[] = [];\n  const allOptionalFields: (keyof ExecutorConfig)[] = [\n    'model',\n    'configDir',\n    'reasoningEffort',\n    'serviceTier',\n    'sandboxMode',\n    'timeoutSeconds',\n  ];\n\n  for (const field of allOptionalFields) {\n    if (!supportedFlags.includes(field) && config[field] !== null && !(field === 'timeoutSeconds' && config[field] === 900)) {\n      unsupportedFields.push(field);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (unsupportedFields.length > 0) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: unsupportedFields.map((field) => ({\n        path: [field],\n        message: `field '${field}' is not supported by executor kind '${config.kind}'. Supported fields for ${config.kind}: ${\n          supportedFlags.length ? supportedFlags.join(', ') : 'none'\n        }.`,\n      })),\n    });\n  }\n\n  return config;\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve an executor configuration by merging CLI and file sources.\n *\n * @param sources - CLI and file partial configs (CLI takes precedence).\n * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n */\nexport function resolveExecutorConfig(sources: {\n  cli?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n  file?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n}): ExecutorConfig {\n  const merged = {\n    ...(sources.file ?? {}),\n    ...(sources.cli ?? {}),\n  };\n  return parseExecutorConfig(merged);\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 6. FAN-OUT CONFIG\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n//\n// Opt-in layer ABOVE the single-executor path. When a fan-out config is present,\n// the loop runs N executor \"lineages\" concurrently (capped), each running the\n// existing sequential loop in its own isolated sub-packet. The single-executor\n// path (executorConfigSchema / parseExecutorConfig) is untouched and remains the\n// default; callers use EITHER a single `executor` OR a `fanout` block, never both.\n\nconst LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN = /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/;\n\n/**\n * One fan-out lineage: a single executor config plus fan-out metadata.\n *\n * - `label`: directory-safe id for the lineage's isolated sub-packet.\n * - `count`: number of replicas of THIS config to run (e.g. 5x the same model).\n * - `iterations`: per-lineage max-iterations override; null = packet default.\n * - `promptFramework`: optional per-model prompt framing key (e.g. \"costar\",\n *   \"tidd-ec\") resolved against sk-prompt-models when a consumer renders the\n *   lineage prompt. null = consumer default. Loop-type-agnostic and optional, so\n *   research/review lineages that omit it are unaffected.\n * - `assignment_model`: defaults to the existing flat pool; `wave` is accepted\n *   only so the runtime guard can reject activation attempts explicitly.\n * - `depends_on` / `touches`: reserved dependency and path-domain metadata for\n *   a future guarded planner; flat-pool execution ignores them after logging.\n */\nexport const lineageExecutorSchema = executorConfigSchema.extend({\n  label: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n    message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":376,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","time":{"start":1783487622240,"end":1783487622247}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0de149b52702f4dc016a4ddc8626a08191b4f1929f12a050af"}},"id":"prt_f40256c59001OABQluv1Dgucwr","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40254971001h40TnOofSDUzcL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487622253,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Ogf8w50aAFdfjSAQgoqXNlDC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","offset":260,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n260:     message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n261:   }),\n262:   count: z.number().int().positive().default(1),\n263:   iterations: z.number().int().positive().nullable().default(null),\n264:   promptFramework: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n265:   assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n266:   depends_on: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n267:   touches: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n268: });\n269: \n270: export type LineageExecutor = z.infer<typeof lineageExecutorSchema>;\n271: \n272: export const fanoutConfigSchema = z.object({\n273:   executors: z.array(lineageExecutorSchema).min(1),\n274:   assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n275:   concurrency: z.number().int().positive().default(2),\n276:   maxRetries: z.number().int().nonnegative().default(5),\n277:   // Stall detection defaults ON: a lineage that stops emitting progress is aborted and\n278:   // requeued within the ceiling and fails loud, instead of hanging silently at 0% CPU\n279:   // until the hours-scale subprocess timeout. Set 0 to opt out.\n280:   lagCeilingMs: z.number().int().nonnegative().default(300000),\n281:   progressHeartbeatSeconds: z.number().nonnegative().default(60),\n282: });\n283: \n284: export type FanoutConfig = z.infer<typeof fanoutConfigSchema>;\n285: \n286: /**\n287:  * Parse and validate a raw fan-out configuration.\n288:  *\n289:  * Each entry's executor subset is routed through {@link parseExecutorConfig} so\n290:  * ALL existing kind/model/flag rules apply per lineage with zero duplication.\n291:  * Labels must be unique and base-label (count>1) expansion must not collide.\n292:  *\n293:  * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n294:  * @returns Validated FanoutConfig.\n295:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n296:  */\n297: export function parseFanoutConfig(raw: unknown): FanoutConfig {\n298:   const parsed = fanoutConfigSchema.safeParse(raw);\n299:   if (!parsed.success) {\n300:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({ issues: parsed.error.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: issue.path, message: issue.message })) });\n301:   }\n302: \n303:   const config = parsed.data;\n304: \n305:   // Reuse the canonical single-executor validator per entry (kind/model/flags).\n306:   config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n307:     const {\n308:       label: _label,\n309:       count: _count,\n310:       iterations: _iterations,\n311:       promptFramework: _promptFramework,\n312:       assignment_model: _assignmentModel,\n313:       depends_on: _dependsOn,\n314:       touches: _touches,\n315:       ...executorSubset\n316:     } = entry;\n317:     try {\n318:       parseExecutorConfig(executorSubset);\n319:     } catch (err: unknown) {\n320:       if (err instanceof ExecutorConfigError) {\n321:         throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n322:           issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['executors', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n323:         });\n324:       }\n325:       throw err;\n326:     }\n327:   });\n328: \n329:   // Labels must be unique among the declared lineages.\n330:   const seenLabels = new Set<string>();\n331:   config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n332:     if (seenLabels.has(entry.label)) {\n333:       throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n334:         issues: [{ path: ['executors', index, 'label'], message: `duplicate lineage label '${entry.label}'` }],\n335:       });\n336:     }\n337:     seenLabels.add(entry.label);\n338:   });\n339: \n340:   // Expanded labels (count>1 → label-1, label-2, …) must not collide either.\n341:   const expandedLabels = new Set<string>();\n342:   for (const lineage of expandLineages(config)) {\n343:     if (expandedLabels.has(lineage.label)) {\n344:       throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n345:         issues: [{ path: ['executors'], message: `expanded lineage label '${lineage.label}' collides; rename base labels` }],\n346:       });\n347:     }\n348:     expandedLabels.add(lineage.label);\n349:   }\n350: \n351:   return config;\n352: }\n353: \n354: /**\n355:  * Expand a fan-out config into concrete per-replica lineages.\n356:  *\n357:  * A `count` of 1 keeps the base label; `count > 1` yields `${label}-1` …\n358:  * `${label}-N`. Each expanded lineage carries `count: 1` so downstream\n359:  * consumers see one runnable unit per element.\n360:  *\n361:  * @param config - Validated FanoutConfig.\n362:  * @returns Flat list of single-replica lineages (one runnable unit each).\n363:  */\n364: export function expandLineages(config: FanoutConfig): LineageExecutor[] {\n365:   const lineages: LineageExecutor[] = [];\n366:   for (const entry of config.executors) {\n367:     if (entry.count === 1) {\n368:       lineages.push({ ...entry, count: 1 });\n369:       continue;\n370:     }\n371:     for (let replica = 1; replica <= entry.count; replica += 1) {\n372:       lineages.push({ ...entry, label: `${entry.label}-${replica}`, count: 1 });\n373:     }\n374:   }\n375:   return lineages;\n376: }\n\n(End of file - total 376 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n  }),\n  count: z.number().int().positive().default(1),\n  iterations: z.number().int().positive().nullable().default(null),\n  promptFramework: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n  depends_on: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n  touches: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n});\n\nexport type LineageExecutor = z.infer<typeof lineageExecutorSchema>;\n\nexport const fanoutConfigSchema = z.object({\n  executors: z.array(lineageExecutorSchema).min(1),\n  assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n  concurrency: z.number().int().positive().default(2),\n  maxRetries: z.number().int().nonnegative().default(5),\n  // Stall detection defaults ON: a lineage that stops emitting progress is aborted and\n  // requeued within the ceiling and fails loud, instead of hanging silently at 0% CPU\n  // until the hours-scale subprocess timeout. Set 0 to opt out.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","text":"    message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n  }),\n  count: z.number().int().positive().default(1),\n  iterations: z.number().int().positive().nullable().default(null),\n  promptFramework: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n  depends_on: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n  touches: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n});\n\nexport type LineageExecutor = z.infer<typeof lineageExecutorSchema>;\n\nexport const fanoutConfigSchema = z.object({\n  executors: z.array(lineageExecutorSchema).min(1),\n  assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n  concurrency: z.number().int().positive().default(2),\n  maxRetries: z.number().int().nonnegative().default(5),\n  // Stall detection defaults ON: a lineage that stops emitting progress is aborted and\n  // requeued within the ceiling and fails loud, instead of hanging silently at 0% CPU\n  // until the hours-scale subprocess timeout. Set 0 to opt out.\n  lagCeilingMs: z.number().int().nonnegative().default(300000),\n  progressHeartbeatSeconds: z.number().nonnegative().default(60),\n});\n\nexport type FanoutConfig = z.infer<typeof fanoutConfigSchema>;\n\n/**\n * Parse and validate a raw fan-out configuration.\n *\n * Each entry's executor subset is routed through {@link parseExecutorConfig} so\n * ALL existing kind/model/flag rules apply per lineage with zero duplication.\n * Labels must be unique and base-label (count>1) expansion must not collide.\n *\n * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n * @returns Validated FanoutConfig.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n */\nexport function parseFanoutConfig(raw: unknown): FanoutConfig {\n  const parsed = fanoutConfigSchema.safeParse(raw);\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({ issues: parsed.error.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: issue.path, message: issue.message })) });\n  }\n\n  const config = parsed.data;\n\n  // Reuse the canonical single-executor validator per entry (kind/model/flags).\n  config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n    const {\n      label: _label,\n      count: _count,\n      iterations: _iterations,\n      promptFramework: _promptFramework,\n      assignment_model: _assignmentModel,\n      depends_on: _dependsOn,\n      touches: _touches,\n      ...executorSubset\n    } = entry;\n    try {\n      parseExecutorConfig(executorSubset);\n    } catch (err: unknown) {\n      if (err instanceof ExecutorConfigError) {\n        throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n          issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['executors', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n        });\n      }\n      throw err;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Labels must be unique among the declared lineages.\n  const seenLabels = new Set<string>();\n  config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n    if (seenLabels.has(entry.label)) {\n      throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n        issues: [{ path: ['executors', index, 'label'], message: `duplicate lineage label '${entry.label}'` }],\n      });\n    }\n    seenLabels.add(entry.label);\n  });\n\n  // Expanded labels (count>1 → label-1, label-2, …) must not collide either.\n  const expandedLabels = new Set<string>();\n  for (const lineage of expandLineages(config)) {\n    if (expandedLabels.has(lineage.label)) {\n      throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n        issues: [{ path: ['executors'], message: `expanded lineage label '${lineage.label}' collides; rename base labels` }],\n      });\n    }\n    expandedLabels.add(lineage.label);\n  }\n\n  return config;\n}\n\n/**\n * Expand a fan-out config into concrete per-replica lineages.\n *\n * A `count` of 1 keeps the base label; `count > 1` yields `${label}-1` …\n * `${label}-N`. Each expanded lineage carries `count: 1` so downstream\n * consumers see one runnable unit per element.\n *\n * @param config - Validated FanoutConfig.\n * @returns Flat list of single-replica lineages (one runnable unit each).\n */\nexport function expandLineages(config: FanoutConfig): LineageExecutor[] {\n  const lineages: LineageExecutor[] = [];\n  for (const entry of config.executors) {\n    if (entry.count === 1) {\n      lineages.push({ ...entry, count: 1 });\n      continue;\n    }\n    for (let replica = 1; replica <= entry.count; replica += 1) {\n      lineages.push({ ...entry, label: `${entry.label}-${replica}`, count: 1 });\n    }\n  }\n  return lineages;\n}","lineStart":260,"lineEnd":376,"totalLines":376,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","time":{"start":1783487622249,"end":1783487622252}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0de149b52702f4dc016a4ddc8626ac81918a4ce05f0a1990c9"}},"id":"prt_f40256c60001Cv5W0ndZlqjte1","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40254971001h40TnOofSDUzcL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487622267,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kOg7HmAjyJoLKt2nqjFcZ0z4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md","offset":52,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n52: ---\n53: \n54: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n55: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n56: \n57: ### Problem Statement\n58: `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` is a fully shipped, unit-tested pure-function library (`resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`/`validateFallbackGraph`, confirmed via direct code read) implementing exactly the \"model A fails, route to model B in a different quota pool\" pattern the operator asked for on `001-reference-research`'s GLM-5.2 → MiMo-v2.5-Pro lineage. It has **zero callers** outside its own test file — `fanout-pool.cjs` only implements same-model retry-with-backoff (`maxRetries`), never a model swap.\n59: \n60: ### Purpose\n61: Wire `resolveFallback()` into `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch: on `retryCount >= maxRetries` (or a specific `failureKind`), look up a `ModelRegistry` and re-dispatch a *new* lineage with the fallback model instead of continuing to retry the failed one.\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n67: ## 3. SCOPE\n68: \n69: ### In Scope\n70: - A `ModelRegistry` config (or inline registry) with at least `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` (confirmed-valid edge: different `quota_pool`s, no cycle, within default max-1-hop).\n71: - `fanout-pool.cjs` retry-exhausted branch calling `resolveFallback()` and re-dispatching.\n72: \n73: ### Out of Scope\n74: - Any change to `fallback-router.ts` itself — it's already correct and tested.\n75: - A general-purpose fallback UI/config surface beyond what this one use case needs.\n76: \n77: ### Files to Change\n78: \n79: | File Path | Change Type | Description |\n80: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n81: | `runtime/lib/deep-loop/` or a new small config file | Create | `ModelRegistry` with the glm-5.2/mimo-v2.5-pro edge |\n82: | `runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Edit | Call `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion, re-dispatch fallback lineage |\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n88: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n89: \n90: ### P2 - Optional (can defer with documented reason)\n91: \n92: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n93: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n94: | REQ-001 | GLM-5.2 lineage auto-substitutes MiMo-v2.5-Pro on retry exhaustion | A forced-failure test on a `glm52` replica produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement replica, not a fourth same-model retry |\n95: | REQ-002 | `fallback-router.ts` itself remains unmodified | The module's own existing unit tests still pass unchanged |\n96: | REQ-003 | Fallback substitution is logged/attributable | A re-dispatched fallback replica's label makes clear it substituted for a failed `glm52-N` replica, not silently indistinguishable |\n97: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n102: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n103: \n104: - **SC-001**: `fallback-router.ts` has a real, non-test caller.\n105: - **SC-002**: 001-reference-research's own GLM-5.2 lineage (if this lands before that phase re-runs) no longer needs the manual operator-mediated re-dispatch workaround documented in `001-reference-research/plan.md`.\n106: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n111: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n(Showing lines 52-111 of 124. Use offset=112 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n`deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` is a fully shipped, unit-tested pure-function library (`resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`/`validateFallbackGraph`, confirmed via direct code read) implementing exactly the \"model A fails, route to model B in a different quota pool\" pattern the operator asked for on `001-reference-research`'s GLM-5.2 → MiMo-v2.5-Pro lineage. It has **zero callers** outside its own test file — `fanout-pool.cjs` only implements same-model retry-with-backoff (`maxRetries`), never a model swap.\n\n### Purpose\nWire `resolveFallback()` into `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch: on `retryCount >= maxRetries` (or a specific `failureKind`), look up a `ModelRegistry` and re-dispatch a *new* lineage with the fallback model instead of continuing to retry the failed one.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- A `ModelRegistry` config (or inline registry) with at least `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` (confirmed-valid edge: different `quota_pool`s, no cycle, within default max-1-hop).\n- `fanout-pool.cjs` retry-exhausted branch calling `resolveFallback()` and re-dispatching.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md","text":"---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n`deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` is a fully shipped, unit-tested pure-function library (`resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`/`validateFallbackGraph`, confirmed via direct code read) implementing exactly the \"model A fails, route to model B in a different quota pool\" pattern the operator asked for on `001-reference-research`'s GLM-5.2 → MiMo-v2.5-Pro lineage. It has **zero callers** outside its own test file — `fanout-pool.cjs` only implements same-model retry-with-backoff (`maxRetries`), never a model swap.\n\n### Purpose\nWire `resolveFallback()` into `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch: on `retryCount >= maxRetries` (or a specific `failureKind`), look up a `ModelRegistry` and re-dispatch a *new* lineage with the fallback model instead of continuing to retry the failed one.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- A `ModelRegistry` config (or inline registry) with at least `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` (confirmed-valid edge: different `quota_pool`s, no cycle, within default max-1-hop).\n- `fanout-pool.cjs` retry-exhausted branch calling `resolveFallback()` and re-dispatching.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Any change to `fallback-router.ts` itself — it's already correct and tested.\n- A general-purpose fallback UI/config surface beyond what this one use case needs.\n\n### Files to Change\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `runtime/lib/deep-loop/` or a new small config file | Create | `ModelRegistry` with the glm-5.2/mimo-v2.5-pro edge |\n| `runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Edit | Call `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion, re-dispatch fallback lineage |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n### P2 - Optional (can defer with documented reason)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | GLM-5.2 lineage auto-substitutes MiMo-v2.5-Pro on retry exhaustion | A forced-failure test on a `glm52` replica produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement replica, not a fourth same-model retry |\n| REQ-002 | `fallback-router.ts` itself remains unmodified | The module's own existing unit tests still pass unchanged |\n| REQ-003 | Fallback substitution is logged/attributable | A re-dispatched fallback replica's label makes clear it substituted for a failed `glm52-N` replica, not silently indistinguishable |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: `fallback-router.ts` has a real, non-test caller.\n- **SC-002**: 001-reference-research's own GLM-5.2 lineage (if this lands before that phase re-runs) no longer needs the manual operator-mediated re-dispatch workaround documented in `001-reference-research/plan.md`.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES","lineStart":52,"lineEnd":111,"totalLines":124,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md","time":{"start":1783487622265,"end":1783487622267}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0de149b52702f4dc016a4ddc8626b48191ab341bf42c246e23"}},"id":"prt_f40256c69001dxT92RNRaoF9Ra","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40254971001h40TnOofSDUzcL"}}
