{"type":"text","timestamp":1783487817394,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"id":"prt_f40284d27001X54TxaUL08m5B3","messageID":"msg_f40283c09001GmmtB0k8wImXtW","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","type":"text","text":"JSON validation passed. All five research questions are now answered, so I’m doing a final low-novelty convergence validation rather than opening a new investigation branch.","time":{"start":1783487810855,"end":1783487817393},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_01c1a0b00bb4b01e016a4ddd42dbd8819196d19247044a90c9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487817449,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uXzTedrOzdToqi4xkk37q3bI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":160},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy\n2: \n3: ## Research Topic\n4: \n5: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n6: \n7: ## Known Context\n8: \n9: - Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n10: - Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n11: - `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n12: - This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n13: - Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n14: \n15: ## Key Questions\n16: \n17: - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n18: - [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n19: - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n20: - [x] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n21: - [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n22: \n23: ## Answered Questions\n24: \n25: - `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n26: - The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n27: - The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n28: - The external reference migration plan is directionally complete across the major live surfaces; keep its staged category model, synchronize advisor projection/codegen/drift guards, regenerate compiled command contracts, and explicitly dedupe duplicate graph edges such as `cli-opencode`.\n29: - `fallback-router.ts` should remain optional/deferred for the core merge; if implemented, amend child 004 to wire model substitution in `fanout-run.cjs` or through an explicit pool hook, add a fallback registry/config surface, emit attribution events, and test GLM-to-MiMo re-dispatch.\n30: \n31: ## What Worked\n32: \n33: - Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n34: - Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n35: - Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n36: - Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n37: - Current-file verification prevented stale-gaps from being carried forward; the 003 plan already includes `sk-prompt`, pre-commit/GitHub Actions mirror paths, and advisor codegen staging.\n38: - Separating `fanout-pool.cjs` from `fanout-run.cjs` clarified that generic retry mechanics and model-aware dispatch are different layers.\n39: \n40: ## What Failed\n41: \n42: - No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n43: - Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n44: - The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n45: - External reference inventory alone does not prove plan gaps; generated outputs, live source assets, routing fixtures, and historical docs need category-specific decisions.\n46: - Child 004's single-file pool edit is under-specified because it omits fan-out config parsing and the runner's model-aware command construction context.\n47: \n48: ## Exhausted Approaches\n49: \n50: - None yet.\n51: \n52: ## Ruled-Out Directions\n53: \n54: - Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n55: - Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n56: - Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n57: - Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n58: - Hand-editing compiled command contracts is ruled out; update source command assets/router files and rerun contract compilation.\n59: - Treating fallback-router wiring as required for rename/unification closeout is ruled out; it is useful optional feature work.\n60: - Wiring model substitution directly into the generic pool without an explicit hook is ruled out; the runner owns model/kind/session/artifact context.\n61: \n62: ## Non-Goals\n63: \n64: - Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n65: - Do not rename `/deep:*` commands or agent names as part of the recommendation unless evidence shows a blocking contradiction.\n66: \n67: ## Stop Conditions\n68: \n69: - Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n70: \n71: ## Next Focus\n72: \n73: Convergence validation and synthesis readiness: confirm all key questions are answered, check residual risk, then produce final synthesis if no new investigation remains.\n\n(End of file - total 73 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n- Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n- [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n- [x] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- Target spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Artifact dir is explicitly bound by `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- This lineage is read-only with respect to source code and spec docs; writes are restricted to this lineage artifact dir.\n- Parent phase says the merge should rename `deep-loop-workflows` to `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, preserve `/deep:*` commands and agent names, repair both relative-path directions, migrate advisor/doctor/agent/docs references, and leave fallback-router wiring optional.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\n- [x] Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\n- [x] Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\n- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\n\n## Answered Questions\n\n- `system-deep-loop/runtime/` is structurally coherent if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not a mode packet; fresh-authored unified graph metadata should replace the current two-skill graph identity.\n- The Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct, but phase 002 should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs`, explicit deep-review shims, and a classified runtime unit-test inventory.\n- The four listed system-spec-kit borrow edits are necessary but incomplete for phase 002 gates; add `runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, `runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts`, and `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts`.\n- The external reference migration plan is directionally complete across the major live surfaces; keep its staged category model, synchronize advisor projection/codegen/drift guards, regenerate compiled command contracts, and explicitly dedupe duplicate graph edges such as `cli-opencode`.\n- `fallback-router.ts` should remain optional/deferred for the core merge; if implemented, amend child 004 to wire model substitution in `fanout-run.cjs` or through an explicit pool hook, add a fallback registry/config surface, emit attribution events, and test GLM-to-MiMo re-dispatch.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Initial packet read established the scoped design, phase sequence, and no-code-change requirement for this lineage.\n- Hub, registry, and graph metadata reads confirmed the merge removes an existing duplicate identity while preserving stable `/deep:*` and agent surfaces.\n- Paired before/after path reasoning on live imports confirmed the proposed hop-count asymmetry and found one unlisted internal executable path.\n- Validation-gate tracing found hidden depth-sensitive files by following `test:council` and the artifact-root re-export, not just the plan's file table.\n- Current-file verification prevented stale-gaps from being carried forward; the 003 plan already includes `sk-prompt`, pre-commit/GitHub Actions mirror paths, and advisor codegen staging.\n- Separating `fanout-pool.cjs` from `fanout-run.cjs` clarified that generic retry mechanics and model-aware dispatch are different layers.\n\n## What Failed\n\n- No hidden structural blocker found; exact graph metadata content still needs review after the physical move.\n- Raw grep is too noisy for migration ownership because it mixes live imports, fixture expectations, generated command-contract inputs, and historical prose.\n- The phrase `tooling-borrow` under-described the artifact-root shared resolver seam; this is a runtime dependency seam, not only compiler/test wiring.\n- External reference inventory alone does not prove plan gaps; generated outputs, live source assets, routing fixtures, and historical docs need category-specific decisions.\n- Child 004's single-file pool edit is under-specified because it omits fan-out config parsing and the runner's model-aware command construction context.\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n- None yet.\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Implementing merge/fallback changes during this research lineage is out of scope.\n- Treating `runtime/` as a workflow mode is ruled out because `mode-registry.json` only models public workflow modes and backend kinds.\n- Blind replacement across all `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` hits is ruled out; executable paths, generated contracts, advisor labels, and history need separate handling.\n- Decoupling runtime from system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling is ruled out for this merge; repair path depth now and leave full decoupling as hardening.\n- Hand-editing compiled command contracts is ruled out; update source command assets/router files and rerun contract compilation.\n- Treating fallback-router wiring as required for rename/unification closeout is ruled out; it is useful optional feature work.\n- Wiring model substitution directly into the generic pool without an explicit hook is ruled out; the runner owns model/kind/session/artifact context.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Do not modify source code, command assets, agents, specs outside this lineage, or routing corpus files.\n- Do not rename `/deep:*` commands or agent names as part of the recommendation unless evidence shows a blocking contradiction.\n\n## Stop Conditions\n\n- Stop after legal convergence once all key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations have run, or at `maxIterations=10`.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nConvergence validation and synthesis readiness: confirm all key questions are answered, check residual risk, then produce final synthesis if no new investigation remains.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":73,"totalLines":73,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783487817444,"end":1783487817448}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c1a0b00bb4b01e016a4ddd495ac8819183f01d2f072f2691"}},"id":"prt_f402866c2001LMTfsKscoN5I1a","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40283c09001GmmtB0k8wImXtW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487817502,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_XSAQD9YGofxmJ8MmEz6LISwR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n3:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"question\": \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime/ structural layout correct, or does it create mode/skill identity ambiguity?\",\n6:       \"answer\": \"Yes, if runtime is kept as non-routable infrastructure under the hub and the unified skill has exactly one graph-metadata identity.\"\n7:     },\n8:     {\n9:       \"question\": \"Are the Class A and Class B path-repair rules complete and directionally correct for live source files and tests?\",\n10:       \"answer\": \"The direction rules are correct, but the concrete phase-002 inventory should add replay-graph-from-artifacts, deep-review shims, and a classified runtime-test list.\"\n11:     },\n12:     {\n13:       \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped to phase 002, and are there hidden borrow paths beyond the four planned files?\",\n14:       \"answer\": \"The four listed borrow edits are phase-002 work, but the plan should add artifact-root.cjs, artifact-root.vitest.ts, and council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts for the planned gates.\"\n15:     },\n16:     {\n17:       \"question\": \"Is the external reference migration plan complete across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, skill graph, generated contracts, and examples?\",\n18:       \"answer\": \"The child 003 plan is directionally complete across the major live surfaces; it should preserve category staging, synchronize advisor codegen/drift guards, regenerate compiled command contracts, and dedupe literal graph-edge duplicates such as cli-opencode.\"\n19:     },\n20:     {\n21:       \"question\": \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain optional/deferred?\",\n22:       \"answer\": \"Keep it optional/deferred for the core merge. If the operator chooses to land it, amend child 004 so model substitution is implemented in fanout-run.cjs or through an explicit pool hook, with a fallback registry/config surface, attribution events, and a forced-failure GLM-to-MiMo integration test.\"\n23:     }\n24:   ],\n25:   \"keyFindings\": [\n26:     {\n27:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f001\",\n28:       \"title\": \"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n29:       \"summary\": \"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\",\n30:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]\n31:     },\n32:     {\n33:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\n34:       \"title\": \"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\n35:       \"summary\": \"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\",\n36:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:16\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:101\"]\n37:     },\n38:     {\n39:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\n40:       \"title\": \"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\n41:       \"summary\": \"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\",\n42:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\"]\n43:     },\n44:     {\n45:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\n46:       \"title\": \"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\n47:       \"summary\": \"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\",\n48:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:51\"]\n49:     },\n50:     {\n51:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\n52:       \"title\": \"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\n53:       \"summary\": \"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\",\n54:       \"sources\": [\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"]\n55:     },\n56:     {\n57:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\n58:       \"title\": \"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\n59:       \"summary\": \"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\",\n60:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\"]\n61:     },\n62:     {\n63:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\n64:       \"title\": \"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\n65:       \"summary\": \"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\",\n66:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"]\n67:     },\n68:     {\n69:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f008\",\n70:       \"title\": \"External migration plan is directionally complete and category-driven\",\n71:       \"summary\": \"The 003 plan covers hardcoded constants, structured identity fields, codegen, command assets, docs, graph metadata, examples, advisor corpus, and final verification as separate categories.\",\n72:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:106\"]\n73:     },\n74:     {\n75:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f009\",\n76:       \"title\": \"Advisor projection migration must be synchronized\",\n77:       \"summary\": \"Python, TypeScript scorer files, and the drift guard all hardcode the merged deep skill identity and registry/projection contract.\",\n78:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:26\"]\n79:     },\n80:     {\n81:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f010\",\n82:       \"title\": \"Hook, CI, plugin, and doctor surfaces are live migration targets\",\n83:       \"summary\": \"The mirror checker, GitHub workflow, loop guard, and parent-skill doctor checker all contain old deep-loop paths or assumptions.\",\n84:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/hooks/pre-commit:40\", \"file:.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml:17\", \"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35\", \"file:.opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/parent-skill-check.cjs:79\"]\n85:     },\n86:     {\n87:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f011\",\n88:       \"title\": \"Sibling graph migration should dedupe duplicate cli-opencode edges\",\n89:       \"summary\": \"The migration should preserve meaningful contextual edges while collapsing literal duplicate targets.\",\n90:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/graph-metadata.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/graph-metadata.json:22\"]\n91:     },\n92:     {\n93:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f012\",\n94:       \"title\": \"fallback-router is shipped and validates fallback graphs\",\n95:       \"summary\": \"The router validates graph safety and resolves failed models to fallback or fail-fast decisions.\",\n96:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:320\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\"]\n97:     },\n98:     {\n99:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f013\",\n100:       \"title\": \"router unit tests do not prove fanout GLM/MiMo integration\",\n101:       \"summary\": \"Pure routing behavior is tested, but there is no forced-failure fanout test for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro.\",\n102:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:36\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:109\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:143\"]\n103:     },\n104:     {\n105:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f014\",\n106:       \"title\": \"fanout-pool only requeues same-label retries\",\n107:       \"summary\": \"The retry branch increments retryCounts and pushes the same item index back to the queue.\",\n108:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]\n109:     },\n110:     {\n111:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f015\",\n112:       \"title\": \"model-aware fallback belongs in fanout-run or an explicit pool hook\",\n113:       \"summary\": \"fanout-run owns lineage model/kind, prompt, command construction, and failure context.\",\n114:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1432\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]\n115:     },\n116:     {\n117:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f016\",\n118:       \"title\": \"GLM to MiMo fallback is optional feature work, not merge-critical\",\n119:       \"summary\": \"The feature needs a registry/config surface and integration test, and the phase is explicitly P2 optional.\",\n120:       \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:272\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:90\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:113\"]\n121:     }\n122:   ],\n123:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n124:     {\n125:       \"approach\": \"Make runtime a mode packet\",\n126:       \"reason\": \"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\"\n127:     },\n128:     {\n129:       \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\n130:       \"reason\": \"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, generated contract inputs, and historical/prose text.\"\n131:     },\n132:     {\n133:       \"approach\": \"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\n134:       \"reason\": \"Path repair is needed now; full compiler dependency decoupling is separate hardening and would conflate validation failures.\"\n135:     },\n136:     {\n137:       \"approach\": \"Hand-edit compiled command contracts\",\n138:       \"reason\": \"Compiled contracts are generated output; source command assets and router files should be edited, then compile-command-contracts.cjs should regenerate the markdown.\"\n139:     },\n140:     {\n141:       \"approach\": \"Treat fallback-router wiring as required for merge closeout\",\n142:       \"reason\": \"The phase is P2 optional and needs config/schema/integration-test work unrelated to rename/path/reference migration.\"\n143:     },\n144:     {\n145:       \"approach\": \"Wire model substitution directly into the generic pool without a hook\",\n146:       \"reason\": \"fanout-pool.cjs only owns generic items/retries; model-aware command construction and lineage context live in fanout-run.cjs.\"\n147:     }\n148:   ],\n149:   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n150:   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n151:   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n152:   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n153:   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n154:   \"metrics\": {\n155:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n156:     \"openQuestions\": 0,\n157:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n158:     \"keyFindings\": 16,\n159:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.95,\n160:     \"coverageBySources\": {\n161:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\": 4,\n162:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\": 3,\n163:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json\": 2,\n164:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs\": 1,\n165:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs\": 2,\n166:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1,\n167:       \".opencode/