   \"title\": \"Runtime should be nested infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n      \"summary\": \"The hub/runtime split already claims a single workflow identity over a consumed backend; merging runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime preserves that architecture.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f002\",\n      \"title\": \"Fresh-authored unified graph metadata is safer than merging two graph files\",\n      \"summary\": \"Runtime graph metadata currently duplicates edges back to workflows; fresh authoring removes now-internal edges.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:16\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:101\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f003\",\n      \"title\": \"Class A and Class B path-direction rules are correct\",\n      \"summary\": \"Runtime-to-workflows keeps hop count and deletes the sibling segment; workflows-to-runtime loses one hop and targets runtime/.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f004\",\n      \"title\": \"replay-graph-from-artifacts is an unlisted internal repair site\",\n      \"summary\": \"The council graph replay script hardcodes the runtime upsert path and should be repaired in phase 002 with internal executable paths.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:51\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f005\",\n      \"title\": \"Runtime unit-test inventory needs explicit classification\",\n      \"summary\": \"Ten unit-test files mention deep-loop-workflows; the plan should classify code-path fixtures separately from historical text.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"command:rg -l deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f006\",\n      \"title\": \"artifact-root is a hidden system-spec-kit seam\",\n      \"summary\": \"artifact-root.cjs re-exports system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs through a depth-sensitive path and must be repaired in phase 002.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f007\",\n      \"title\": \"test:council needs council-playbook-anchor-integrity path updates\",\n      \"summary\": \"The test:council script includes council-playbook-anchor-integrity, which hardcodes deep-loop-runtime test paths and regexes.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:27\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f008\",\n      \"title\": \"External migration plan is directionally complete and category-driven\",\n      \"summary\": \"The 003 plan covers hardcoded constants, structured identity fields, codegen, command assets, docs, graph metadata, examples, advisor corpus, and final verification as separate categories.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:106\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f009\",\n      \"title\": \"Advisor projection migration must be synchronized\",\n      \"summary\": \"Python, TypeScript scorer files, and the drift guard all hardcode the merged deep skill identity and registry/projection contract.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:26\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f010\",\n      \"title\": \"Hook, CI, plugin, and doctor surfaces are live migration targets\",\n      \"summary\": \"The mirror checker, GitHub workflow, loop guard, and parent-skill doctor checker all contain old deep-loop paths or assumptions.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/hooks/pre-commit:40\", \"file:.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml:17\", \"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35\", \"file:.opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/parent-skill-check.cjs:79\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f011\",\n      \"title\": \"Sibling graph migration should dedupe duplicate cli-opencode edges\",\n      \"summary\": \"The migration should preserve meaningful contextual edges while collapsing literal duplicate targets.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/graph-metadata.json:31\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/graph-metadata.json:22\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f012\",\n      \"title\": \"fallback-router is shipped and validates fallback graphs\",\n      \"summary\": \"The router validates graph safety and resolves failed models to fallback or fail-fast decisions.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:320\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f013\",\n      \"title\": \"router unit tests do not prove fanout GLM/MiMo integration\",\n      \"summary\": \"Pure routing behavior is tested, but there is no forced-failure fanout test for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:36\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:109\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:143\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f014\",\n      \"title\": \"fanout-pool only requeues same-label retries\",\n      \"summary\": \"The retry branch increments retryCounts and pushes the same item index back to the queue.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f015\",\n      \"title\": \"model-aware fallback belongs in fanout-run or an explicit pool hook\",\n      \"summary\": \"fanout-run owns lineage model/kind, prompt, command construction, and failure context.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1432\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\", \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-6-f016\",\n      \"title\": \"GLM to MiMo fallback is optional feature work, not merge-critical\",\n      \"summary\": \"The feature needs a registry/config surface and integration test, and the phase is explicitly P2 optional.\",\n      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:272\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:90\", \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:113\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Make runtime a mode packet\",\n      \"reason\": \"The registry models public workflow modes only; runtime is backendKind infrastructure and packet-level graph metadata is prohibited.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide replacement for path coupling\",\n      \"reason\": \"Grep hits mix executable imports, fixture expectations, generated contract inputs, and historical/prose text.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Decouple runtime from system-spec-kit compiler/typeRoots during the merge\",\n      \"reason\": \"Path repair is needed now; full compiler dependency decoupling is separate hardening and would conflate validation failures.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Hand-edit compiled command contracts\",\n      \"reason\": \"Compiled contracts are generated output; source command assets and router files should be edited, then compile-command-contracts.cjs should regenerate the markdown.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Treat fallback-router wiring as required for merge closeout\",\n      \"reason\": \"The phase is P2 optional and needs config/schema/integration-test work unrelated to rename/path/reference migration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Wire model substitution directly into the generic pool without a hook\",\n      \"reason\": \"fanout-pool.cjs only owns generic items/retries; model-aware command construction and lineage context live in fanout-run.cjs.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"observedIdeas\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n    \"keyFindings\": 16,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.95,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\": 4,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\": 3,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json\": 2,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs\": 2,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts\": 3,\n      \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md\": 5,\n      \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py\": 3,\n      \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts\": 1,\n      \".opencode/hooks/pre-commit\": 1,\n      \".github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml\": 1,\n      \".opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js\": 1,\n      \".opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/parent-skill-check.cjs\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/graph-metadata.json\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt/graph-metadata.json\": 1,\n      \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md\": 1,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts\": 4,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts\": 4,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs\": 4,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\": 5,\n      \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts\": 1,\n      \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md\": 3,\n      \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md\": 1\n    }\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":191,"totalLines":191,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1783487817472,"end":1783487817496}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c1a0b00bb4b01e016a4ddd495ae08191852a3b0f817b1249"}},"id":"prt_f402866f5001pmP7uYSsyrL8OI","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40283c09001GmmtB0k8wImXtW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487817502,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_HlgDl0H1h1srUfBJYYHt0icY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard\n2: \n3: ## Iteration Table\n4: \n5: | run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |\n6: |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n7: | 1 | Structural layout and identity model | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n8: | 2 | Bidirectional path-coupling repair | 0.85 | 6 | complete |\n9: | 3 | System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams | 0.80 | 6 | complete |\n10: | 4 | External reference migration completeness | 0.70 | 5 | complete |\n11: | 5 | Fallback-router real wiring decision | 0.75 | 5 | complete |\n12: \n13: ## Question Status\n14: \n15: 5 / 5 answered.\n16: \n17: ## Convergence Trend\n18: \n19: 0.90 -> 0.85 -> 0.80 -> 0.70 -> 0.75. All key questions are answered; one low-novelty convergence validation pass remains before synthesis.\n20: \n21: ## Dead Ends\n22: \n23: - Treating raw old-name grep results as directly actionable is a dead end; categories need separate handling.\n24: - Hand-editing compiled command contracts is ruled out; regenerate them from source command assets.\n25: - Treating fallback-router wiring as a mandatory merge dependency is ruled out.\n26: - Wiring model-aware fallback directly into the generic pool without an explicit hook is ruled out.\n27: \n28: ## Blocked Stops\n29: \n30: - None.\n31: \n32: ## Graph Convergence\n33: \n34: - Not evaluated for this detached lineage.\n35: \n36: ## Next Focus\n37: \n38: Convergence validation and synthesis readiness.\n\n(End of file - total 38 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Structural layout and identity model | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Bidirectional path-coupling repair | 0.85 | 6 | complete |\n| 3 | System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams | 0.80 | 6 | complete |\n| 4 | External reference migration completeness | 0.70 | 5 | complete |\n| 5 | Fallback-router real wiring decision | 0.75 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n5 / 5 answered.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n0.90 -> 0.85 -> 0.80 -> 0.70 -> 0.75. All key questions are answered; one low-novelty convergence validation pass remains before synthesis.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Structural layout and identity model | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Bidirectional path-coupling repair | 0.85 | 6 | complete |\n| 3 | System-spec-kit tooling borrow and hidden seams | 0.80 | 6 | complete |\n| 4 | External reference migration completeness | 0.70 | 5 | complete |\n| 5 | Fallback-router real wiring decision | 0.75 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n5 / 5 answered.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n0.90 -> 0.85 -> 0.80 -> 0.70 -> 0.75. All key questions are answered; one low-novelty convergence validation pass remains before synthesis.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Treating raw old-name grep results as directly actionable is a dead end; categories need separate handling.\n- Hand-editing compiled command contracts is ruled out; regenerate them from source command assets.\n- Treating fallback-router wiring as a mandatory merge dependency is ruled out.\n- Wiring model-aware fallback directly into the generic pool without an explicit hook is ruled out.\n\n## Blocked Stops\n\n- None.\n\n## Graph Convergence\n\n- Not evaluated for this detached lineage.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nConvergence validation and synthesis readiness.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":38,"totalLines":38,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-6/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1783487817476,"end":1783487817498}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c1a0b00bb4b01e016a4ddd495ae88191b58814cedce10c40"}},"id":"prt_f402867020012usFE9RL6CHi9V","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66cbffe4XyuwEMaxiBvG7","messageID":"msg_f40283c09001GmmtB0k8wImXtW"}}
